Commentary: Starts with a length ball just outside off, Zak Crawley covers his line and lets it go. Naseem Shah starts with a dot.

FOUR! England and Zak Crawley are away. Good length again, outside off. Zak Crawley looks to block it with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence for a boundary!
Fuller one on middle, Zak Crawley flicks it to square leg for a brace.
FOUR! Zak Crawley gets in double figures soon. Fuller and on off, Zak Crawley knocks it through long off for a boundary.
FOUR! Back to back boundaries. On a length and on off, Zak Crawley stays firm and punches it through long off for another boundary. 14 off the over already!
On a length and on off, Crawley goes for a block but the ball kisses the inner part of the bat and rolls on the leg side. A dot to end with.
FOUR! England are dealing in boundaries here. Slightly shorter and outside off, Ben Duckett hangs back and slaps it through point for a boundary. He gets off the mark in style.
Fuller one on middle, Ben Duckett defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off this time, Ben Duckett looks to slap it but misses.
Good length and angling it into the batter, Ben Duckett defends it out solidly.
Bowls it down leg, Ben Duckett flicks it to short mid-wicket. Looks for a single but Zak Crawley sends his back.
This one lands outside off, fuller in length. Ben Duckett plays it with soft hands towards deep point for a brace.

Loud appeal for LBW! Pakistan are confident, but the umpire is not interested. At the moment there is no DRS. On a length and on middle and leg, Zak Crawley looks to flick it but misses as the ball hits his pads. He gets a lucky escape.
Fuller one on off, Zak Crawley guides it to point for a brace.
Another LBW appeal turned down. Bowls it on a length and on off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone as the ball nips back in and kisses his pads. An appeal for lbw but umpire is unmoved.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Zak Crawley blocks it away.
Fuller again, on off. Zak Crawley lunges and defends it out.
This one lands outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Bowls it outside leg, Ben Duckett looks to flick it but misses. The keeper gets his glove on it diving to his right. They collect two byes.
FOUR! Beautifully timed. Fuller and on leg, Ben Duckett flicks it into the gap through square leg for a boundary!
On a length and on off, Ben Duckett taps it but finds the fielder at point.
On a length and on middle, Ben Duckett flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Goes fuller and on off, Ben Duckett defends it with soft hands back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Ben Duckett eases it straight towards the fielder at covers.
On a length and outside off, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
On a length, angling it into the batter with some extra bounce. Zak Crawley looks to defend it but gets a hit on his thigh and rolls back towards the bowler.
Good length again, Zak Crawley defends it out solidly.
Touch fuller this time, outside off. Zak Crawley taps it towards the fielder at point.

FOUR! Good length and just outside off, Zak Crawley looks to drive it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball just misses the stumps and races away the fine leg fence. Lucky boundary. That was close!
Pulls his length back immediately. Short of a length and Zak Crawley reads it well and blocks it solidly.
Mohammad Ali starts the over from 'round the wicket to the left-hander. He bowls this full and just outside the off pole, Ben Duckett defends this back towards the bowler.
Angled into the stumps on a good length, Ben Duckett gets behind the line of the ball and blocks this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! There is a boundary coming every over for England! This is on a good length as well and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett plays the ball late and guides it through the backward point region for four runs.
He strays onto the pads this time on a fuller length, Ben Duckett clips this towards deep square leg and they take two runs as the fielder gives chase and stops the ball.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett knocks this towards the point fielder.
Goes fuller this time and just outside the off pole, Ben Duckett defends this solidly back down the pitch to the left of the bowler. 6 runs from this over.
Naseem Shah bowls this full and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley mistimes his shot towards short cover.
Gets this closer to the stumps on a good length, Zak Crawley blocks this towards mid on.

FOUR! Naseem Shah bowls a surprise bouncer and Zak Crawley reacts instantly! This is directed into the batter who pulls and gets a top edge that flies towards the fine leg fence for four runs. There was a fielder positioned there but the ball is a little to straight and he is unable to get to it.
Goes fuller this time and on an off stump line, Zak Crawley pushes this towards the mid on fielder.
Gets this wider outside the off pole and on a good length, Zak Crawley pushes this towards mid off.
Gets the ball to nip back in slightly from a good length and just outside off, Zak Crawley is watchful as he blocks this solidly.
Haris Rauf begins his journey in Test cricket with a full delivery served outside the off stump, Ben Duckett digs this out towards point.
Goes full once again and this time pitching on an off stump line, Ben Duckett knocks this towards cover point.
Bowls this in line with the stumps and on a fuller length, Ben Duckett clips this to the left of mid-wicket and collects a single.
Continues bowling full and attacking the stumps, Zak Crawley manages to flick this towards square leg and they take another run.
Decides to bowl this on a good length and on a middle stump line, Ben Duckett defends this firmly back towards the bowler.
On a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett taps this to the right of point and a slight misfield from the fielder allows them to take a single.
Naseem Shah bowls this full and on the pads, Ben Duckett clips this past the mid-wicket fielder and the batters collect two more runs.
Delivers this in line with the stumps on a good length, there is no movement in this wicket. Ben Duckett defends this with ease back towards the bowler.

FOUR! There is not much conviction in this shot but it will be a boundary nonetheless! Naseem Shah serves this full and outside the off pole, Ben Duckett swings his bat at the ball and gets a thickish outside edge through the vacant gully region for a boundary to deep backward square leg.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett defends this towards cover.
Bowls this one a touch fuller and in line with the stumps, Ben Duckett hits it straight back and dismantles the stumps at the non-striker's end.
On a good length once again and outside off, Ben Duckett continues to defend and plays this towards mid off.
Haris Rauf begins the over with a full delivery in line with the stumps. Zak Crawley hits this firmly down the pitch but the bowler collects it.
Continues bowling full and on an off stump line, Zak Crawley defends this towards mid on.
FOUR! That is a cracking shot! Haris Rauf bowls one on a good length and outside the off pole, Zak Crawley hits this on the up and drives the ball to deep cover for four runs.

FOUR! Two boundaries in a row now and England are off to a flier! Haris Rauf compensates by going full on the pads, Zak Crawley picks this off easily and clips it towards deep mid-wicket for four more runs. England have reached 61 even before the 10th over has been completed.
Strays on the pads once again on a fuller length, Zak Crawley flicks this towards deep square leg and some good fielding in the deep saves another boundary and restricts the batters to two runs.
Bangs in a vicious bouncer in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley considers going for the pull shot but decides against it at the last moment.
Bowls it flatter and on leg, Ben Duckett flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
Another leg break outside the off and Ben Duckett drives it towards the extra cover for another double.
On off, Ben Duckett clips it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett looks to sweep it but gets his ribs. A stifled appeal turned down.
FOUR! Well connected. Bowls it on off, Ben Duckett plays a reverse sweep through backward point for a boundary!
FOUR! Back to back boundaries. This one lands down leg, Ben Duckett shuffles across and scoops it through fine leg for another boundary!
Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
FOUR! Easy pickings. Good length and just outside leg, Zak Crawley uses the pace of the ball and just gives it a fine tickle as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
On a length and on off, Zak Crawley defends it away.
FOUR! England are dealing in boundaries here. Short of a length and on off, Zak Crawley hangs back and pulls it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Back of a length once again outside the channel. Zak Crawley bends low and lets it alone.
FOUR! 12 off the over. Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley pulls it through mid-wicket for four more. Excellent timing!
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett eases it towards short covers.
Slightly shorter with a hint of turn, Ben Duckett looks to sweep it but misses. Close!
Fuller one, on off. Ben Duckett uses his feet and nudges it towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder chases it well. They collect three runs.
FOUR! This one lands on off, Zak Crawley leans forward for the paddle and helps it through fine leg for a boundary. Fifty up for Zak Crawley!
Fuller and on middle, Zak Crawley defends it well.
Full and around off. Zak Crawley leans forward and paddles it towards the fine leg. Haris Rauf at the edge of fine leg dives forward and saves the boundary. Three taken!
Fuller one and on middle, Zak Crawley flicks it towards square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Ben Duckett defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Ben Duckett defends it to point.
Good length and on off, slower too. Ben Duckett taps it towards point for one.

NO BALL AND THREE RUNS! Full and on the middle stump. Zak Crawley drives it past the mid on fielder. Haris Rauf chases it well and stops it before the fence. The batters complete three runs and look for the fourth but decide against it. 100 up for England and what a start it has been for them! Mohammad Ali has overstepped and he will have to bowl an extra delivery in this over.
Good length and outside off, Ben Duckett punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
Fuller one and on off. Ben Duckett lunges forward and pushes it to covers.
Flatter and on off, Zak Crawley flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Zak Crawley moves forward and pushes a fuller ball towards mid-wicket. Dot.
Drops the length short a bit. Zak Crawley goes back and pulls it towards the deep backward square leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Full and angling it into the batter. Ben Duckett sweeps but gets a top edge that carries towards backward square leg and drops in no man's land. They collect one.
Fuller and on off, Zak Crawley eases it to mid off.
On a length and on middle. Zak Crawley drives it to mid on. Dot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
FOUR! Zak Crawley is onto this in flash! Mohammad Ali bowls this back of a length and into the batter, Zak Crawley pulls this off his body towards deep backward square leg for a boundary.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley defends this solidly towards cover.

Goes a touch fuller this time outside off, Zak Crawley strokes this firmly towards the cover fielder. He collects and throws the ball at the non-striker's end. There is a direct hit but the batter is inside the crease and the ball ricochets towards mid off for a run eventually.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps, Ben Duckett goes on the back foot and clips the ball towards mid-wicket. A misfield allows the batters to take two runs.

FOUR! Zak Crawley is collecting boundaries for fun here! Zahid Mahmood bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley goes deep in the crease and punches the ball into the mid-wicket region for four runs.
Bowls full and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes really full and into the pads, Zak Crawley almost yorks himself but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Fuller and on off, Zak Crawley knocks it towards the fielder at mid off.
This is full as well and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley blocks this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! Second boundary in the over! Zahid Mahmood bowls short once again and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley uses the depth of the crease well and plays the ball to wide long on for four more runs.
Mohammad Ali bowls this from 'round the wicket and angled this in from outside off, Ben Duckett blocks this towards mid off.
NO BALL! Goes full this time and outside the off pole, Ben Duckett looks to play at this but keeps his bat away. Mohammad Ali has overstepped and it will be a no ball.

FOUR! Ben Duckett is now one run away from his half-century! Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length but offers width. Ben Duckett cuts this late towards deep backward square leg and gets himself a boundary.
That will be FIFTY for Ben Duckett and this opening partnership is definitely flourishing! This is on a good length as well and outside off, Ben Duckett taps this towards point and takes one.
This is slightly full and on an off stump line, Zak Crawley gets across and clips the ball towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this on a good length and angling down leg, Zak Crawley pushes at the ball and gets beaten on the inside edge as the ball thumps against his pads.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley defends this towards mid on.
Zahid Mahmood flights a full delivery in line with the stumps from' round the wicket. Ben Duckett taps the ball towards mid on with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Goes over the wicket to the right-hander and serves this full outside off, Zak Crawley pushes this toward cover-point and takes one.
Bowls this full and on the pads, Ben Duckett clips this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Zahid Mahmood floats this one full and straight, Ben Duckett opts to go for the reverse sweep and finds the deep point fielder. They take a single.
Goes full once again and just outside off, Zak Crawley flicks this towards mid on.

FOUR! Zak Crawley looks in sublime form! Zahid Mahmood floats another full delivery outside off, Zak Crawley knocks this past the mid on fielder this time and collects a boundary as the ball races to the long on fence for four more runs.

FOUR! This has been slapped away! Haris Rauf comes into the attack and bowls a short ball from 'round the wicket. The ball sits up nicely for Ben Duckett who pulls the ball towards the mid-wicket fence for four runs.
This is on a good length and outside off, Ben Duckett guides this towards deep backward point for a single.
Goes full this time and angles this in from just outside off, Zak Crawley defends the ball back down the pitch.
Continues bowling full and angles this into the stumps, Zak Crawley clips the ball towards deep backward square leg for a run.
Strays onto the pads this time on a fuller length, Ben Duckett flicks this to the left of mid on and they rush across for a single.
This is ona good length and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley defends this towards the leg side.
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett taps it bit finds the fielder at covers.
Another one on off, this is defended towards covers.
Flatter and on off, Ben Duckett slaps it but finds the fielder at point.
Fuller and on middle, defended back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Ben Duckett eases it towards the point fielder.
FOUR! This one lands down leg, Ben Duckett paddles it through fine leg for a boundary!
Good length angling it into the batter, Zak Crawley defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on leg, Zak Crawley looks to flick it but gets his pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Yorker is out, on the middle. Ben Duckett clips it to the square leg fielder.
On a length and on leg, Ben Duckett blocks it to mid on.
On a length and outside off, Ben Duckett plays a square drive to deep backward point and crosses over for a couple of runs.
Another one outside off, Ben Duckett defends it solidly.
Tosses it up on middle, Zak Crawley defends it with soft hands towards mid on.
FOUR! Over pitched and outside leg, Zak Crawley looks to sweep but gets an inside edge. The ball beats the keeper and goes through the fine leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on middle, defended to mid-wicket.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Ben Duckett creams it through extra covers for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, this is defended back towards Ben Duckett.
Another one on off, Ben Duckett drives it to covers for one.
Fuller one on off, Ben Duckett eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Good length shaping it in, Ben Duckett defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on leg, Ben Duckett flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Length ball and on off, Zak Crawley blocks it towards mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Zak Crawley clips it towards backward square leg for one.
Full and on off stump, this is defended back to the bowler.
Fuller one on off, Zak Crawley flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Over-pitched and outside off, Ben Duckett drives it but doesn't connect well. The ball goes to the fielder at mid-off.
Full nad on off, this is defended towards mid off.
FOUR! Half volley and on middle, Ben Duckett flicks it into the gap though square leg for a boundary. Excellent timing!
Back of a length outside off, Ben Duckett pushes it to deep point for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley defends it solidly.
Full and on the middle stump, Ben Duckett pushes it to mid off.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Ben Duckett looks to pull it but doesn't connect well. It rolls to the right of the keeper.
Good length and on off, Ben Duckett guides it to point for one.
Back of a length and on the off stump, Zak Crawley pushes it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Wide! A wayward bouncer, Zak Crawley lets it go. Wide called.

FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley heaves it through mid-wicket. The fielder at mid on runs and dives to take a catch but just couldn't reach it. The ball races away for a boundary. Zak Crawley moves to 90 now!
Fuller one on off, Zak Crawley eases it to mid-wicket. Dot.
Good length and on the leg stump, this is pushed to the man at mid on.
Good length and on off, Ben Duckett eases it to covers.
Bowls it outside off, Ben Duckett cuts it towards point for one.
Fuller and on off, Zak Crawley drives it to covers. A misfield allows the batters to steal a run.
On a length and on off, Ben Duckett defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Ben Duckett flicks it to mid-wicket. England ends their wonderful first session at 174 for none!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Zak Crawley drives it towards deep extra covers. The fielder does well to stop it. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, this is played towards deep extra covers for one.
Fuller again, Ben Duckett defends it back towards Zahid Mahmood.
Good length on the middle stump, Ben Duckett clips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it to off, Zak Crawley drives it to covers for one more.
Fuller one down leg, Ben Duckett flicks it to mid-wicket for one again.
Good length angling it into the batter, Ben Duckett works it to mid-wicket. Dot.
Touch fuller, on off. Ben Duckett flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Fuller one, on off. Zak Crawley opens the face of his bat and guides it into the gap and through point for a boundary. He moves to 99 now!

NOT OUT!  Full and nipping back in, Zak Crawley looks to flick it but misses and the ball hits the pads. The Pakistan players all go up in appeal and the umpie raises his finger. Zak Crawley checks with his partner and asks if it going down leg, eventually decides to go upstairs. UltraEdge indicates that there is no inside edge. Ball tracking shows two reds and one green as the ball is the leg stump. Zak Crawley survives on 99 as the onfield decison has to be reversed. Ben Stokes is smiling in the pavilion and is probably happy that DRS is back.
On a length and on off, Zak Crawley defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! He gets to his century in style! A full ball on the off stump, Zak Crawley creams it through covers for a boundary!
Full on the leg stump, this is clipped to deep square leg for a single.
Good length and on off, Zak Crawley drives it to covers for one.
FOUR! Excellent timing on this. Fuller one and on middle, Ben Duckett picks the length early on and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett drives it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Zak Crawley punches it to long off for one.

Naseem Shah bowls this full and outside off, Zak Crawley strokes this towards deep cover for a single. Brings up the 200-run partnership between these two which is the highest opening stand for England against Pakistan.
Goes 'round the wicket to the southpaw. Bowls this full and into the pads, Ben Duckett clips this towards mid-wicket.
Full once again and in line with the stumps, Ben Duckett blocks this solidly back towards the bowler.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett defends this towards the cover fielder.
Goes full once again and outside the off pole, Ben Duckett strokes this to the right of mid off and takes one.
Naseem Shah serves this on a yorker length and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley digs this out towards mid on.
Zahid Mahmood floats this full and just outside off, Ben Duckett premeditates and goes for the reverse sweep. Hits the ball to deep point and takes a single.
Goes full once again and just outside off, Zak Crawley clips this towards mid on.
Continues to flight this full and into the batter, Zak Crawley clips this one towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Strays onto the pads on a fuller length, Zak Crawley tucks this towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
This is the first ball that has done something off the wicket! Zahid Mahmood floats this full and just outside off, Zak Crawley pushes at the ball but gets beaten by just a hint of spin.
Goes full once again and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley defends this back down the pitch to the bowler's right.

FOUR! Haris Rauf is greeted back into the attack with a boundary! Haris Rauf bowls from 'round the wicket and tries to bang this into the pitch outside off. Ben Duckett gets well on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep square leg for four runs.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Ben Duckett blocks this back towards the bowler.
Bowls this outside the off stump on a good length once again, Ben Duckett cuts this to deep point and takes a single.
Goes full and attacks the stumps, Zak Crawley flicks the ball straight to mid-wicket.
Full once again and outside the off pole, Zak Crawley strokes this to the right of mid off.

FOUR! Zak Crawley is feeding off the Pakistan bowlers here! Haris Rauf pulls his length back slightly and offers width outside off. Zak Crawley goes back in the crease and creams it towards deep cover-point for a boundary.
Zahid Mahmood bowls this short and outside off, Ben Duckett cuts this late towards deep backward point and takes one.
Goes full and outside off, Zak Crawley taps this towards point.

FOUR! Slashed away for a boundary! Zahid Mahmood bowls this slightly short and outside off, Zak Crawley goes hard at the ball and gets a thickish edge past the slip fielder for a boundary to third man.
Bowls this full and outside the off stump, Zak Crawley gets his front foot forward defends the ball towards cover.
Slights this one full and in line with the stumps, Zak Crawley blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Goes really full this time outside the off pole, Zak Crawley flat bats this towards deep point for a single and will keep strike.
Haris Rauf bowls this on a good length and outside off, Zak Crawley works this to deep backward point and they run well to complete two runs.
Bangs this in short and in line with the stumps. Zak Crawley ducks under this slightly but the ball is well over his head as it goes through to the keeper.
Another short ball served outside the off stump, Zak Crawley pulls this well to the left of deep square leg where the fielder does well to restrict the batters to a single.
Goes short once again and into the batter, Ben Duckett mistimes his pull towards mid-wicket.

FOUR! That is a HUNDRED for Ben Duckett as well! What an inning this has been from a man making his comeback! Haris Rauf continues bowling short and attacking the batters, Ben Duckett gets over the bounce and pulls this to deep backward square leg past the diving fielder for four runs.
Haris Rauf sticks to bowling short and it seems to be the new tactic. Ben Duckett is happy to pull this away to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett looks to reverse sweep but gets a top edge towards covers. They collect two.
FOUR! Full on middle, this is swept away through deep square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Ben Duckett looks to sweep it but misses.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan finally have a breakthrough in the game and the massive opening partnership has been broken! Zahid Mahmood gets a wicket on his debut and he is ecstatic. He floats this full and gets it to pitch on an off stump line. Ben Duckett attempts the reverse sweep but does not connect and the ball hits his chest as he stumbles over after the shot. There is a massive appeal from the players around the bat but the umpire remains unmoved. Zahid Mahmood looks convinced and Babar Azam indulges by going for the review. There is no bat involved as confirmed by UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows three reds. The on-field decision has to be reversed and England finally lose their first wicket.
Howout: lbw b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: Flatter and on middle, Ollie Pope covers his line and blocks it out.

NOT OUT! Full and on the middle stump. Pope does not read the googly and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal there by the bowler again. Once again the umpire says no and Pakistan take the review. There is no edge on this and the Ball Tracking shows umpires call on two occasions and the decision remains. Ollie Pope survives but needs to be careful now as Pakistan have their tail up all of a sudden.
Full and on off, Zak Crawley eases it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller again, on off. Zak Crawley flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Bowls it on off, Zak Crawley taps it to covers. Dot.
Fuller one on off, Zak Crawley knocks it towards the mid on fielder.

OUT! TIMBER! Pakistan get their second in quick time and it is Haris Rauf who strikes this time. Two of the debutants have dismissed both England openers and there will be two new batters at the crease now. This is bowled on a good length and on off, this one nips back in sharply. Zak Crawley looks to drive it but the ball goes in the gap between his pads and the bat to knock the stumps over. Pakistan are back in the game and they will hope to carry on with this momentum. Both the England openers are back in the hut after reaching their centuries!
Howout: b Haris Rauf

Commentary: Fuller one on off, Joe Root defends it out solidly.
FOUR! Fuller one and on off, Ollie Pope reverse sweeps it through third man for a boundary!
On off, this is defended towards the off side.
Another one on off, Ollie Pope covers his line and defends it to point.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope reverse sweeps it through backward point for a boundary!
Good length on off stump, this is pushed to the man at covers.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on middle, Ollie Pope smashes it through mid on. The fielder misfields it which results in a boundary!
On a length and on off, Joe Root punches it to mid off. Dot.
Goes fuller this time, Joe Root eases it to the point fielder.
Fuller again, on off. Joe Root drives it but finds the fielder at extra covers.
Good length angling it into the batter, Joe Root blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller again, on off. Joe Root defends it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Joe Root blocks it to mid off. A maiden from Haris Rauf.
Flatter and on middle, Ollie Pope eases it to covers.
Bowls it down leg, Ollie Pope flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller one and on off, Joe Root taps it to covers. Dot.
Flatter and on middle, Joe Root defends it back towards the bowler.
Good length and on off stump, this is pushed towards covers.
Fuller one, Joe Root tucks it to square leg for one.

FOUR! A boundary right after the break for England! Mohammad Ali bowls a back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Joe Root gets on his toes and punches the ball towards deep backward point for a boundary.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Joe Root taps this towards cover-point and takes a single.

Mohammad Ali goes full this time and angles the ball into the stumps from outside off, Ollie Pope flicks this ball to deep square leg and they take three runs as the fielder chases the ball and collects it.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump, Joe Root defends this towards point.
Another fullish delivery outside off, Joe Root blocks this towards cover and says no loudly to the non-striker.

Mohammad Ali goes straight once again on a good length, Joe Root gets behind the line of the ball and tucks it away towards deep square leg. Naseem Shah cuts off the boundary but the batters complete three runs.

FOUR! That has been played with great control! Zahid Mahmood floats this one full and in line with the stumps, Joe Root goes for the reverse sweep and plays it delicately towards third man for a boundary.
This is slightly short and outside off, Joe Root blocks this towards point.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off stump, Joe Root knocks this towards mid off.
Strays onto the pads on a fuller length, Joe Root looks to sweep this fine but does not connect well and takes a single to short fine leg.
Another fullish delivery served outside the off pole, Ollie Pope taps this towards the off side and takes off for a single.
Loose delivery once again from Zahid Mahmood as he delivers this down leg on a fullish length. Joe Root gets down on one knee and sweeps this towards fine leg for a brace.
Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and just outside  off, Ollie Pope gets across to cover the line of the ball and taps it towards short mid-wicket.

FOUR! This has not been a great debut for Mohammad Ali! He bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps, Ollie Pope plays a short-arm jap and pulls the ball towards deep square leg for four runs.
Goes full this time outside off, Ollie Pope miscues his shot towards the mid off fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump, Ollie Pope taps the ball towards backward point.
Bangs this in short and in line with the stumps, Ollie Pope pulls this towards deep square leg for a single.
Goes a fraction full and outside the off pole, Joe Root looks to drive but gets beaten as the ball stays low.
Zahid Mahmood flights this one full and outside off, Ollie Pope gets a good stride forward and blocks the ball to the left of the bowler.
Gets the ball to drift in from outside off on a fullish length, Ollie Pope gives the bowler a charge but inside edges his short to deep backward square leg for a single.
This is slightly short and wide outside off, Joe Root goes on the back foot and defends this to the off side.
Goes full this time and just outside the off pole, Joe Root shimmies down the wicket and clips the ball past mid-wicket for a single.
Googly this time bowled full and just outside off, Ollie Pope gets his bat down in time and plays it towards point.
Another googly from Zahid Mahmood and this is closer to the stumps, Ollie Pope defends this to the leg side.
Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and outside off, Joe Root looks to guide this to third man but the ball stays low and he edges it onto the ground towards first slip.
This is on a good length as well and keeps bowling in the channel outside off, Joe Root is well behind the line of the ball as he blocks it to the off side.

Joe Root goes for an audacious shot! Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps, Joe Root goes for a switch hit but there is not enough bounce in the wicket. He plays it to the first slip fielder.
Mohammad Ali goes full and into the pads, Joe Root clips this towards deep mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.

FOUR! That is a gorgeous shot from Joe Root! No need to run for that. Mohammad Ali goes a touch fuller and serves this outside off, Joe Root gets his front foot forward and drive the ball into the gap between mid off and cover for four runs.
On a good length and just outside off, Joe Root defends this towards mid on.
Zahid Mahmood flights this full and outside off, Ollie Pope defends this solidly to the left of the bowler.
FOUR! Lovely uses of the feet from Ollie Pope! Zahid Mahmood floats this one full and outside off, Ollie Pope gets to the pitch of the ball and finds the deep cover fence for four runs.
Bowls this quicker in the air but sliding down leg on a shorter length, Ollie Pope looks to tuck this leg side but misses as the ball hits his pads.
Another loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Ollie Pope defends this to the off side.
Zahid Mahmood angles this into the stumps on a fuller length, Ollie Pope taps this towards mid on and takes a quick single.

OUT! PLUMB! That looks straight and Pakistan have the big wicket of Joe Root! Zahid Mahmood has given away 100 runs but has taken two very important wickets in this game so far! Flights this one full and pitches on an off stump line. The ball does not turn and keeps its line to hit Joe Root low on his back leg as he looks to sweep. There is a huge appeal and the umpire lifts his finger instantly. They have reviewed this and UltraEdge confirms there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows three reds and England will lose their review. The on-field decision stays and Joe Root has to walk back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump, Ollie Pope defends this towards covers.
Gets the ball close to the stumps this time on a good length, Ollie Pope tucks this away towards mid-wicket.
Another ball that nips back in from a good length, Ollie Pope flicks this to the right of mid-wicket and looks for a single but will not make it and decides against it.
Good-length delivery bowled outside the off stump. Ollie Pope looks solid in defense as he keeps this one out.
Goes a fraction full this time outside off, Ollie Pope taps this towards gully.
Back to bowling on a good length and just outside the off stump, Ollie Pope pushes this towards mid on.
Zahid Mahmood drifts one in on a fullish length, Harry Brook blocks this back towards the bowler.
Goes full once again and outside off, Harry Brook shapes up for a paddle sweep but changes his shot and defends the ball towards point.
Flights this one full and into the pads, Harry Brook uses his feet and clips the ball towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Bowls this outside the off stump on a fullish length, Harry Brook looks to work this off side but inside edges the ball back down the pitch.

FOUR! Harry Brook does not want the Pakistan bowlers to get their momentum! Zahid Mahmood flights this full and outside off, Harry Brook charges down the wicket and lofts the ball towards the vacant long on region for four runs.
Another full delivery but straying on the pads this time, Harry Brook paddles this towards fine leg and picks up a couple of runs.
Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and into the stumps, Ollie Pope clips this towards mid-wicket.
Goes fuller this time and outside off, Ollie Pope is tempted into the drive but gets an inside edge towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Another fullish delivery served outside the off pole, Harry Brook looks to cut but the ball is not short enough and he gets beaten.
Bowls it outside off, Harry Brook punches it towards the fielder at covers.

FOUR LEG BYES! Free runs for England here! Mohammad Ali strays onto the pads on a good length, Harry Brook looks to play this fine but misses. He gets some pad on the ball though and it races away to fine leg for four leg byes.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump, Harry Brook blocks this back towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery bowled full and outside off, Ollie Pope strokes this straight to the cover fielder.

FOUR! Ollie Pope has played this really fine! That brings up the 300 for England and we are still in the second session! Zahid Mahmood strays down leg on a fuller length, Ollie Pope gets some bat on this and the ball goes between the keeper's leg for four runs.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Ollie Pope knocks this to long off and takes one.
Another fullish delivery flighted outside off, Harry Brook pushes the ball away and the bowler dives to his left to stop it.

Bowls this one short and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook uses the depth of the crease and pulls this towards deep square leg. The ball goes to the fielder in the deep and they have to settle for a single.
This is slightly short as well and straight, Ollie Pope goes on the back foot and defends this to the right of the bowler.
On a length and outside leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it but misses.
Good length again, on off. Harry Brook defends it solidly off the front foot.
Sticks to his length and on middle, Harry Brook flicks it to short mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Length and outside off, Ollie Pope looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence. Lucky boundary!
Bowls it on middle, Ollie Pope flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter and on off, Ollie Pope pulls it towards square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope eases it towards the mid off fielder.
On off, defended to covers.
This one lands down leg, Ollie Pope loos to flick it but mistimes it. It carries towards leg slip. The fielder makes a good effort but couldn't grab it. Dot.
Fuller and on off, ths is defended towards mid on.
Fuller one, Ollie Pope prods and pushes it back to the bowler.
Keeps it fuller again as Pope pushes this down to the covers.
Tossed up, on middle. Harry Brook defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, this is again defended towards Saud Shakeel.
On off this time, Harry Brook eases it to short covers.
FOUR! Finds the gap. Fuller and on middle, Harry Brook flicks it through mid-wicket. The fielder chases it but the ball wins the race.
Fuller and on middle, Harry Brook eases it to mid-wicket for one.
Another fuller ball, Ollie Pope knocks it to mid on for one.
Slightly shorter one, Ollie Pope flicks it to square leg for one.
Tossed up, on middle. Brook eases it back towards the bowler.
SIX! Zahid Mahmood errs in his line and Brook was ready for it. Slightly shorter and on off, Harry Brook smashes it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum!
This one lands on off, Harry Brook cuts it to point for one.
FOUR! Bowls it down leg, Ollie Pope just gives it a fine tickle as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Fuller one and on off, Ollie Pope nudges it to mid-wicket for one. That will be Tea break on Day 1.
On a length and on off, Ollie Pope defends it to short mid-wicket.
Good length again, outside off. Ollie Pope eases it towards the fielder at gully.
Goes fuller this time, Ollie Pope works it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller and outside off, Ollie Pope taps it to covers for one.
On a length and outside off, Harry Brook shoulders arms at it.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook defends it to the man at backward point.
FOUR! Zahid Mahmood has been welcomed with a boundary after the break! Floats this one full and outside off, Ollie Pope sweeps this well towards deep square leg for a boundary.
Flights this one full and well outside the off stump, Ollie Pope attempts the reverse sweep this time but misses.
Floats this one wide outside off on a fuller length, Ollie Pope pope reaches for the ball and strokes it to deep cover-point for a single.
Another loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Harry Brook knocks this past the cover fielder and takes a single as the ball goes to the deep.
This is full as well and outside the off stump, Ollie Pope taps this with soft hands towards cover-point and takes a quick single.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off, Harry Brook looks to cut but gets an under edge towards point.
On a length and on leg, Ollie Pope flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Naseem Shah bowls this full as well and wide outside off, Harry Brook shimmies down the wicket and looks to drive but gets an inside edge to deep backward square leg for a single.
Naseem Shah is looking for reverse swing but not getting his line right. This is wide outside off as well on a fullish length, Ollie Pope plays this to extra cover and take one more.
This is on a good length and outside off, Harry Brook punches this towards deep point and takes a single.
Bowls full once again and outside the off pole, Ollie Pope finds the cover fielder this time.

FOUR! Brings up the 350 for England with lovely wristwork! Naseem Shah goes straight this time on a fuller length, Ollie Pope clips this through the vacant mid-wicket region and the ball races away to the fence for four runs.

FOUR! Harry Brook exhibiting how to use the wrists as well! Zahid Mahmood bowls this a fraction short and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook stays back in the crease and flicks the ball to deep mid-wicket for four more runs.
Bowls this one full and outside off, Harry Brook drives this to deep cover-point and takes a single.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside off, Ollie Pope guides this to deep backward point and takes a couple of runs.

FOUR! Second boundary in the over and this time from the bat of Ollie Pope! Zahid Mahmood bowls this short and outside off, Ollie Pope uses the depth of the crease and cuts this towards deep backward point for four runs.
Bowls this full and outside off, quicker through the air. Ollie Pope raises his bat and leaves this one alone.
Goes straighter this time and continues bowling full, Ollie Pope clips this to deep mid-wicket and takes a single to keep strike. 12 runs have come from the over.
Naseem Shah bowls a full delivery just outside the off stump, Ollie Pope clips this towards the mid on fielder.
This is on a good length and on an off stump line, Ollie Pope defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes full once again and attacks the stumps, Ollie Pope flicks this off his pads towards deep square leg for a single.
Aiming for the off pole on a fullish length, Harry Brook blocks this solidly back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Really full this time outside the off stump, Harry Brook knocks this to the left of mid off and takes one.
Continues bowling outside off stump on a good length, Ollie Pope pushes this towards mid off.
Zahid Mahmood floats this one full and outside off, Harry Brook looks to cut but the ball stays low and he mistimes his shot to cover.
Another full delivery outside off, Harry Brook nudges the ball to long on for a single.
This is on the pads on a fuller length, Ollie Pope flicks this to deep backward square leg for a run.
Slightly short and outside off, Harry Brook punches this towards deep point and takes one more.
Drifting into the pads on a fuller length, Ollie Pope clips this with soft hands towards deep mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs.
Flighted delivery bowled full and well outside off, Ollie Pope eases the ball to long off and takes a single to keep strike.
On a length and on leg, Ollie Pope flicks it to square leg for a brace.
FOUR! Fuller one this time, Ollie Pope clips it in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Good length angling it in, Ollie Pope defends it to mid on.
Length again, on off. Ollie Pope taps it to short covers and scampers through for a single.
FOUR! On a length and on leg, Harry Brook flicks it through fine leg. The fielder makes an attempt to stop it at fine leg but just couldn't stop it. It races away for a boundary!
On a length and outside leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it but misses.
Length ball, on off. Ollie Pope whips it towards mid-wicket for one.
Slower through the air and on off. Harry Brook defends it away.
A single as this is played towards square leg.
Fuller one, Ollie Pope plays a reverse sweep towards backward point for a brace.
Slightly shorter one and on off. Ollie Pope flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Harry Brook reaches his maiden Test match half-century! Agha Salman bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook flicks the ball towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Serves it down leg, Ollie Pope flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Another one down leg, Harry Brook helps it to fine leg for one again.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope creams it through covers for a boundary. He moves to 91.
Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope eases it to mid on for one.
Good length and outside the off stump, Harry Brook shoulder arms at it.
A yorker and outside off, Harry Brook looks to drive it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the keeper.
FOUR! Excellent timing. Fuller and on off, Ollie Pope moves forward and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Full and on off, this is pushed to mid off for a single.
Fuller and on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Full and on the leg stump, this is pushed to mid-wicket. Dot.
Slightly shorter one, Harry Brook reverse paddles it to backward point for one.
On off, Ollie Pope plays it to mid off for one.
Fuller one and on off, Ollie Pope clips it to mid on for one. He moves to 99 now!
On a length and on leg, Harry Brook flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Harry Brook looks to pull it but misses.
SIX! Slightly shorter and on off, Harry Brook hangs back and heaves it over mid-wicket for a maximum. He moves to 48 now!
Fuller and on leg, Harry Brook clips it to backward square leg for one. So, Harry Brook moves to 49 and Ollie Pope is on 99 now!
Good length and on off, Ollie Pope defends it to extra covers. Dot.
Harry Brook reaches his maiden FIFTY in Test cricket! Agha Salman bowls this full and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook flicks this to deep mid-wicket for a single to reach the landmark.

Ollie Pope reaches his HUNDRED now and removes his helmet to celebrate! This is drifted into the pads on a fuller length, Ollie Pope clips the ball to deep square leg for a single. All his teammates are up on their feet and this has been a wonderful inning to watch.
FOUR! Another reverse sweep gathers a boundary for Harry Brook! This is full and outside off, Harry Brook smashes this to the deep point fence for four runs.
Fuller and on off, Harry Brook flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller again, on off. Ollie Pope clips it to square leg for one more.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Harry Brook drives it through covers for a boundary. England move to 422 now. These are the most runs scored in Pakistan in a Day's play!
Good length ball outside off, this is pushed to the backward point fielder.
Another one on off, Ollie Pope plays it to backward point. Dot.
On a good length and outside the off stump, Ollie Pope taps the ball to backward point for a single.
Goes slightly fuller and outside off, The ball stays low but Harry Brook manages to keep this out as he plays it towards point.
Attacks the stump on a fuller length, Harry Brook works this to the leg side straight to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Bowls this back of a length and outside off, Harry Brook punches this to deep point to take a single and keep strike.
FOUR! Harry Brook is not missing out on the loose delivery here! Saud Shakeel bowls this short and outside off, Harry Brook pulls this towards wide long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Harry Brook now! Saud Shakeel over-compensates by bowling a low full toss outside off, Harry Brook strokes this to deep cover for four runs.

FOUR! Make the three! Harry Brook is taking a liking to Saud Shakeel's bowling. This is served full and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook powers this down the ground to the long on fence for four more runs.

FOUR! This is proving to be an onslaught! Four boundaries in four balls! Saud Shakeel bowls this short and outside off, Harry Brook pulls this towards deep mid-wicket and collects another boundary for himself.

FOUR! Five boundaries now and this will be devastating for the bowler's confidence! Bowls this short as well and outside off, Harry Brook rocks back onto the back foot and creams this to deep cover for yet another boundary.

FOUR! That completes an entire over of boundaries! Harry Brook has destroyed Saud Shakeel and taken 24 runs in these six balls! Saud Shakeel keeps bowling short and outside off, Harry Brook pulls this towards wide long on where it all started for the sixth boundary of the over!
This is on a good length and outside the off pole, Ollie Pope blocks this towards mid off.
Back of a length and on the off stump, this is pushed to short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter again, Ollie Pope flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Harry Brook drives it towards covers for one again.
Continues to bowl full and into the pads, Ollie Pope clips the ball towards short mid-wicket.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump, Ollie Pope taps this to the right of covers and takes a single.
Zahid Mahmood floats this one full and outside off, Ollie Pope strokes this towards wide long on and they take two runs.
Goes full and in line with the stumps, Ollie Pope clips this towards long on and takes a single.

FOUR! That has been timed sweetly by Harry Brook! Zahid Mahmood flights this one full and outside the off stump, Harry Brook gets his front foot forward and caresses the ball to deep cover for four runs.
This is full and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook blocks this back down the pitch.
Bowls this one short and outside off, Harry Brook cuts this to deep cover-point and takes a single.
Drifts this one into the pads on a fuller length, Ollie Pope clips this towards short fine leg.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook defends it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook looks to defend it but miscues it to backward square leg. They cross.
On off, Ollie Pope taps it to covers for one more.
Good length angling it in, Harry Brook guides it to point for one.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan have a wicket against the run of play! Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and in line with the stumps. Ollie Pope looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A huge appeal but the finger stays down. Pakistan goes for a review after some contemplation. UltraEdge shows no spike and Ball Tracking shows three reds. The umpire has to reverse his decision and Ollie Pope walks back to the pavilion after scoring an excellent century.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Ali

Commentary: On a length and on off, Stokes defends it solidly.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook drives it towards deep covers for a brace.
Good length angling it into the batter, Harry Brook defends it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Harry Brook clips it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Ben Stokes looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence for a boundary!
FOUR! Length again, on leg. Ben Stokes clips it through mid-wicket for another boundary!
FOUR! This one lands outside off, Ben Stokes opens the face of the bat and guides it through third man for four more!
Fuller and on off, Harry Brook drives it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter and down leg, Stokes fends it to mid-wicket. Dot.
On off, defended out.
Fuller one and on off, Ben Stokes knocks it to mid off for one.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Harry Brook defends it to mid on.
Bowls it down leg, Harry Brook looks to pull it but gets his pads. The ball rolls towards backward square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Harry Brook taps it to backward point for one.
Serves it on middle, Ben Stokes eases it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Ben Stokes pulls it in the gap through square leg. The fielder makes a long chase. They collect three runs.
Bowls it outside off, Harry Brook defends it towards the point fielder.
FOUR! Excellent shot and Harry Brook brings up his century in style! Fuller and on off, Harry Brook gets on his knee and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Fuller again, on off. Harry Brook clips it to short mid-wicket and calls for one but Ben Stokes sends him back. Dot.
FOUR! Ben Stokes joins the party as well. Fuller and on off, Ben Stokes lofts it over mid off for a boundary!
On a length and on leg, Ben Stokes defends it to square leg.
SIX! Fuller one and on off, Ben Stokes heaves it over mid-wicket for a maximum!
FOUR! On a length and outside off, Ben Stokes slaps it through point for a boundary. 500 up for England. What a day for the visitors!
Fuller one and on off, Ben Stokes nudges it but finds the fielder at mid on. Dot.
FOUR! Slightly shorter, Ben Stokes hangs back and plays an upper cut over the keeper and through third man for a boundary. England end the day for 506/4. THAT WILL BE STUMPS FOR DAY 1.
Starts with a length ball down leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it but gets his pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
SIX! Ben Stokes has made a statement here. He starts with a bang. Fuller and on off, Ben Stokes lofts it over long off for a maximum!
Fuller again, Stokes taps it to point for one.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook defends it out to point.
Good length angling it into the batter, Harry Brook eases it to short covers and scampers through for a single.

OUT! TIMBER! Pakistan have an early breakthrough on Day 2 and the skipper of England has to depart! A slower ball does the trick for Naseem Shah. He bowls it on a good length and on middle, looks like an off-cutter. Ben Stokes looks to make room towards the leg side and cut the ball away but gets beaten by the pace. The ball pegs the middle stump back and Stokes walks out for 41 in just 18 balls. Naseem Shah looks pumped as he celebrates and gives the batter a send-off. Just the start Pakistan were looking for and they will have their tail up now.
Howout: b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Flatter one on leg, Harry Brook defends it to square leg.
Slightly shorter and on off, Harry Brook taps it towards the fielder at point.
Fuller this time, this is defended towards the man at mid-wicket.
SIX! All the way. Fuller and on middle, Harry Brook goes with the turn and lofts it over long on for a biggie.
This one lands on off, Harry Brook eases it to point for one.
Flights it around off, Liam Livingstone drives it uppishly to the mid on fielder. A dot to end with.
Touch fuller and on leg, Harry Brook covers his line and blocks it away.
Good length angling it into the batter, Harry Brook defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball as this is defended towards mid on. Good over so far.
On a length and outside leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it but misses.
On a length and outside leg, Harry Brook looks to flick it but misses again.
Good length and outside off, Harry Brook taps it to point for one.
Flatter one on off with a hint of turn, Harry Brook defends it solidly.
Fuller one again, Harry Brook knocks it to long on for one.
Fuller length angling in around off, Liam Livingstone pushes to the cover fielder.
A quicker one pushed through around off, Liam Livingstone defends it back to the bowler.
Liam Livingstone is off the mark. Slightly shorter and on off, Liam Livingstone taps it to covers for one.
Back of a length again, Harry Brook knocks it to deep covers for a brace. Good running!
Good length around off, Liam Livingstone eases it to the cover fielder for one.
On a length and on off, this is again defended to covers.
Goes fuller angling it in, Harry Brook taps it to mid off. Dot again.
Fuller again and on middle and leg, Harry Brook awkwardly defends it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook flicks it to mid on for one.
Good length again, Liam Livingstone defends it to the mid on fielder to end the over.
Bowls it outside off, Harry Brook taps it to point for one.
SIX! Liam Livingstone was holding it back for some time but opens up finally. Fuller and on off, Liam Livingstone moves forward and lofts it over long on for a maximum!
Fuller length around off, Liam Livingstone defends on the front foot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Liam Livingstone taps it to covers for one.
Fuller one this time, on off. Harry Brook nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Tossed up, on off. Harry Brook eases it to mid on. A dot to end the over.

OUT! TAKEN! Pakistan have started this day with positive intent. Bowls it fuller and on leg, Liam Livingstone moves forward to flick it but doesn't connect well. The ball carries at deep square leg. Saud Shakeel settles under it and pouches it around his head. England lose their sixth wicket! Liam Livingstone will be kicking himself as he would have not got a better pitch to make his debut on. Pakistan are clawing themselves back into this game.
Howout: c Saud Shakeel b Naseem Shah

Commentary: NOT OUT! A yorker and on leg, Will Jacks looks to flick it but gets his leg. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Pakistan goes for a review. Fair delivery, Ultra Edge shows no spike. Ball Tracking shows it was missing leg. This will ge a leg bye. Pakistan lose their review.
Naseem Shah bowls a low full toss outside off, Harry Brook knocks this towards cover and takes a quick single.
On a good length and outside off, Will Jacks defends this towards the point fielder.
This is in line with the stumps on a good length, Will Jacks blocks this back down the pitch.
Goes slightly fuller this time and outside the off stump, Will Jacks taps this towards mid on. Another successful over for Pakistan and Naseem Shah has started the day really well.

SIX! Harry Brook has nailed this! Zahid Mahmood goes around the wicket to attack the rough outside the leg stump, but Harry Brook is up to the task. He pulls out a reverse sweep and thumps the ball over deep point for a maximum!
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Zahid Mahmood! Bowls this short and well outside leg, Harry Brook has all the time in the world to sweep this towards deep square leg for four runs.
FOUR! Zahid Mahmood is taking a pounding here! Harry Brook deploys the reverse sweep again and puts away a full delivery outside leg for four more runs towards deep cover-point.
FOUR! Harry Brook is making his intentions clear! Zahid Mahmood goes over the wicket now and bowls this short and outside off, Harry Brook pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for yet another boundary!
SIX! 24 runs in 5 balls for Harry Brook! Zahid Mahmood flights this one full and outside off, Harry Brook uses his feet and thumps the ball over long off for the second six of the over.

Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump, Harry Brook looks to sweep and gets and outside edge over the slip fielder. The ball does not reach the boundary but they take three runs and Harry Brook will be on strike.
FOUR! Harry Brook does not want to stop! Naseem Shah bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps, Harry Brook pulls this towards deep mid-wicket to start the over with a boundary.
This is on a good length as well and he follows the batter to the leg side. Harry Brook looks to make room but does not connect his cut.

FOUR! A little bit of luck for the England batter but the edged boundary gets him to 150! This is bowled slightly full and outside off stump, Harry Brook looks to drive but gets a faint edge that flies between the keeper and first slip. Neither playes made a move for the ball and Harry Brook gets a boundary to third man. He has reached the landmark in just his second Test and what a player he proving to be for England.

OUT! CAUGHT! Harry Brook's enterprising inning comes to an end as he perishes looking to continue his onslaught! Naseem Shah bowls this back of a length and into the batter, Harry Brook goes for the pull shot once again but does not connect this one cleanly. He finds Saud Shakeel at deep square leg who takes another comfortable catch. England have lost their seventh wicket but their intentions are pretty clear this morning.
Howout: c Saud Shakeel b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Goes for the yorker to welcome the new batter and serves this in line with the stumps, Ollie Robinson digs this out towards the bowler.
Bowls this full and into the stump, Ollie Robinson looks to work it leg side but gets a leading edge to cover.
Zahid Mahmood flights this one full and outside off, Will Jacks pushes at this but gets beaten by the turn.
Slightly short and in line with the stumps, Will Jacks eases this down to long on for a single.
Slides this one down leg on a fuller length, Ollie Robinson misses and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Bowls this a fraction short and outside off, Ollie Robinson taps this towards point.
Flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off pole, Ollie Robinson shimmies down the ground and hits the ball to mid on. Good stop by the fielder.
Another ball that slides down leg on a fuller length and it will be a dot ball to end the over.
FOUR! That is a beautiful shot from Will Jacks! Naseem Shah serves this one full and outside the off pole, Will Jacks gets a good stride forward and creams this to deep cover for a boundary.
This is on a good length but straying onto the pads, Will Jacks clips this down to fine leg for a single.
Bowls this short and outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson pulls this towards deep backward square leg and collects one.

Lands just short of the fielder in the deep. Naseem Shah goes fuller this time and on the pads. Will Jacks flicks this ball towards deep backward square leg and the ball lands in front of the fielder. They take a run.
This is on a fullish length as well and just outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson blocks this back to the bowler's left.
Goes full once again but angles this one down leg side, Ollie Robinson misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Flatter one on off, Will Jacks taps it to covers for one.
Bowls it outside off, Ollie Robinson gets in two minds but lets it go in the end.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Ollie Robinson gets on his knee and slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller one and on off, Ollie Robinson defends it to mid on.
On off again, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Flatter one, down leg. Ollie Robinson eases it to the mid on fielder. A dot to end with.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Will Jacks looks to flick it but misses. A stifled appeal turned down.
Slightly shorter one, on leg. Will Jacks pulls it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off, Ollie Robinson steers it to deep covers for a brace.
On a length and on off, Ollie Robinson flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Strays it on the leg stump. Too much leg side. Ollie Robinson misses the flick and it gets him on the pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They cross for a leg bye.
Good length ball, angles it on the middle and leg. Will Jacks flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on. Time for Drinks in Rawalpindi now!
Flatter and on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller nad on middle, Ollie Robinson defends it solidly.
Fuller again, on off. Ollie Robinson steers it to point for one.
Outside off this time, Will Jacks reverse sweeps it. The fielder stops it well at backward point. Dot.
Now a good top by the slip fielder. Full on the off. Will Jacks plays the reverse sweep and the slip fielder gets a hand to it and stops it well.
Slower through the air, slightly fuller. Will Jacks slogs it in the air towards the vacant deep mid-wicket region for a brace.
Good length and on off, Ollie Robinson eases it to covers for one.
On a length and outside off, Will Jacks steers it to point for one.
Fuller one and on off, Ollie Robinson looks to flick it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards the fielder at short mid-wicket. Dot.
Fuller one and on off, Ollie Robinson defends it well back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller, on off. Ollie Robinson eases it to the fielder at mid off.
A dot to end the over. Another fuller and this is defended solidly by Ollie Robinson.
Zahid Mahmood flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Will Jacks eases this to long on for a single. This is the highest score for England against Pakistan in Test cricket!
SIX! This is huge and that is 600 for England! Zahid Mahmood floats another full delivery outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson charges down the wicket and thumps the ball over long on for a maximum.
This is full as well and outside off stump, Ollie Robinson looks to reverse sweep but does not connect well and the ball rolls to slip.
Bowls this just outside off on a fuller length, Ollie Robinson clips this towards mid-wicket.
Looped up and bowled full outside off, Ollie Robinson defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Flighted delivery way outside off, Ollie Robinson slog sweeps this towards deep mid-wicket. Does not time this well but the batters complete three runs.
Mohammad Ali goes full and outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson mishits the ball towards mid-wicket.
This is on a good length and angled into the stump, Ollie Robinson blocks this towards mid on.
Mohammad Ali starts with a really full delivery angling down leg, Ollie Robinson looks to flick this leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.

FOUR! That has been thumped away! Mohammad Ali bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson takes a couple of steps forward and makes room for himself. He wacks this into the gap and finds the deep cover fence for four runs.
Straying down leg side on a slightly shorter length, Ollie Robinson looks to pull but misses and the ball goes through to the keeper.
FOUR! Ollie Robinson is pulling out the long handle here! Mohammad Ali goes fuller and outside the off pole, Ollie Robinson hits this hard towards long on and collects four more runs to his kitty.

Naseem Shah starts with a full delivery in line with the stumps, Will Jacks swings his bat and gets on hand off the handle while playing the shot. Tha ball goes high towards deep point and lands just short of the fielder. The ball went really high and they complete two runs.
Goes full once again and outside off, Will Jacks looking to be aggressive but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
FOUR! Connects this one and collects a boundary! Naseem Shah bowls this slightly short and outside off, Will Jacks cuts this to deep cover and gets four runs.

FOUR! Two boundaries in a row and Will Jacks has decided to show his repertoire of shots! Naseem Shah bowls this full and outside off, Will Jacks lofts this over the infield and finds the long off fence for four more runs.
Angles this into the pads on a good length, Will Jacks misses his clip and gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and they take a leg bye.
Strays onto the pads once again and continues to bowl on a good length, Ollie Robinson flicks the ball to deep square leg for a single.

Mohammad Ali starts the over with a short ball outside off, Ollie Robinson miscues his pull shot and the ball goes high into the air. It lands in the vacant deep mid-wicket region and they take a couple of runs more.
This is on a good length and just outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson blocks this towards mid on.
Bowls this further outside the off pole back of a length, Ollie Robinson taps the ball towards mid on.
On a good length and aimed for the off pole, Ollie Robinson looks to swing leg side but gets an inside edge to deep backward square leg for a single.
Bangs this in short and outside off, Will Jacks gets on top of the bounce and pulls this ball towards deep square leg for a run.
Bowls this back of a length and in line with the stumps, Ollie Robinson looks to make room and swing but mistimes his shot towards mid on.
Naseem Shah bowls a full delivery angled into the stumps, Will Jacks flicks this ball towards deep square leg and collects a single.
This is full as well and aimed for the stumps, Ollie Robinson manages to clip the ball away towards mid-wicket and they take a quick run.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump, Will Jacks defends this towards mid on.
Pulls his length back a fraction and angles this into the pads. Will Jacks tucks the ball to deep backward square leg and takes one.
Decides to go for the short pole outside the off stump, Ollie Robinson is onto it in a flash and pulls the ball towards deep mid-wicket. They take a couple of runs as the fielder cuts the ball off.
On a good length and in line with the stumps, Ollie Robinson blocks the ball back down the pitch towards the bowler.
FOUR! On a length and on off, Will Jacks creams it through covers for a boundary. Lovely piece of timing from Will Jacks!

OUT! TAKEN! Will Jacks's cameo comes to an end! On a length and on off, Will Jacks looks to heave it but mistimes it completely. The ball carries towards short mid-wicket where Naseem Shah takes it comfortably around his head. Mohammad Ali has been rewarded for his effort and England have lost their eighth wicket! It is pretty evident here that they are not looking to play out overs and are aiming to score maximum runs.
Howout: c Naseem Shah b Mohammad Ali

Commentary: On a length and outside off, Jack Leach lets it go. Starts with a dot.

FOUR OVERTHROW RUNS! Fuller and on off, Jack Leach eases it to point and runs for one. Ollie Robinson sends him back. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses and there was no one backing him up. The ball races away the deep square leg fence and Jack Leach is off the mark!
Fuller and on off, Jack Leach defends it solidly.
Good length and on off, Jack Leach blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Ollie Robinson nudges it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Jack Leach fends it to mid off.
On a length and outside off, Jack Leach lets it through towards the keeper.
Bangs a shorter one on leg, Jack Leach leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Jack Leach lets this one go as well.
Good length angling it into the batter, Jack Leach defends it solidly towards mid on.
On a length and on off, Ollie Robinson knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Shorter one this time, Ollie Robinson looks to play an upper cut but misses.
Shorter one on off, Ollie Robinson pulls it towards square leg for one.
Good length ball on the off stump, Leach plays it towards covers with firm hands.
Pulls his length a bit, and bowls in the same line. Jack Leach hangs back and punches it to covers. Dot.
Fuller one this time, this is played towards the mid on fielder.
Fuller and slower too, Ollie Robinson gently flicks it to square leg for a brace.

OUT! LBW! Zahid Mahmood gets his third and Ollie Robinson will have to depart! This is tossed up on middle and leg, Ollie Robinson looks to reverse sweep it but misses and the ball hits his pads. The finger goes up immediately. Ollie Robinson goes upstairs. Ultra Edge shows no spike and Ball Tracking shows that it was just clipping the leg pole. Ollie Robinson has to walk out as the umpire's call stands!
Howout: lbw b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: Fuller and outside off, James Anderson looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, James Anderson flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Jack Leach looks to defend it but misses. It bounces off and goes past his outside edge. Pakistan thinks it was a slight edge but the umpire is unmoved.
Tough chance at first slip. Googly on off, Jack Leach slashes and gets an outside edge as it flies towards Babar Azam who drops it.
Fuller and on off, this is defended solidly.
Slightly shorter one and on off, Jack Leach looks to pull it but doesn't connect well.
A bouncer and outside off, Jack Leach leaves it alone.
Good length angling it into the batter, Jack Leach flicks it to square leg for one.
On a length and outside off, James Anderson looks to defend it but misses.
Short of a length on the off, Jack Leach fends it off the back foot.
Zahid Mahmood flights this on full and down leg side, James Anderson looks to reverse sweep but misses as the keeper collects the ball.
FOUR! Calls of catch it but the ball is far from any fielder. Zahid Mahmood bowls this short and outside off, James Anderson rocks back and cuts this to the deep cover fence for four runs.
Goes full and outside off, James Anderson looks for a reverse sweep once again but misses.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps, James Anderson defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Flights this one full and just outside the off stump, James Anderson gets a stride forward and smothers the ball into the pitch.

OUT! CAUGHT! Zahid Mahmood brings an end to the England inning with his fourth wicket! He flights this one full and outside the off stump, James Anderson looks to drag the ball towards the leg side and goes for the sweep shot. The ball takes the top edge of his bat and goes high towards the square leg region. Imam-ul-Haq runs to his right from backward square leg and takes an easy catch. England have posted a huge total on the board and Pakistan will now have to bat long to save this Test match.
Howout: c Imam-ul-Haq b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: James Anderson bowls his first ball in Pakistan and it is on a good length outside off, Abdullah Shafique dabs it towards point and takes a single to get off the mark.
Goes slightly fuller and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues to attack the stumps on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq defends this back to the bowler's left.
This is angling away from the left-hander on a good length, Imam-ul-Haq leaves this one alone.
Gets this closer to the off pole but still moving away from a good length, Imam-ul-Haq shoulders arms to this one.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this towards mid off. Just one run coming from the first over. Ollie Robinson to bowl from the other end.
Ollie Robinson will bowl from the other end and he starts off with a full delivery angled into the stumps, Abdullah Shafique taps this towards short mid-wicket.
On a good length and wide outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique is watchful as he leaves this alone.
Continues bowling on a good length and on an outside off stump channel, Abdullah Shafique defends this solidly towards mid off.
Angles this into the pads on a good length, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick this to the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There may have been a bit of an inside edge as well.

Ollie Robinson bowls this slightly back of a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique goes deep in the crease and punches the ball towards deep point. Jack Leach gives chase and does well to keep the ball from crossing the ropes. The batters just take two runs and that is poor running from Pakistan.
Bowls a good length delivery to end the over, outside the off pole. Abdullah Shafique gets behind the line of the ball and defends it back towards the bowler.
James Anderson goes full and outside the off pole, Imam-ul-Haq knocks the ball towards cover.
On a good length but straying onto the pads, Imam-ul-Haq clips the ball to deep backward square leg and takes a single.
Goes full this time and serves this outside off, Abdullah Shafique pushes at the ball and gets a thickish edge towards deep point for a couple of runs.
Continues bowling full and in line with the stumps, Abdullah Shafique eases this towards mid on.
On a good length and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique looks to work it leg side but gets a leading edge towards cover.
Attacks the stumps once again on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique taps the ball towards the fielder placed at silly mid on.
Ollie Robinson comes 'round the wicket to the left-hander. He bowls this on a good length and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks the ball towards cover.
Goes full this time into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq defends this back down the pitch and Ollie Robinson moves to his left to stop the ball.
Strays onto the pads on a good length, Imam-ul-Haq tucks the ball towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.
Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and aims for the off pole, Imam-ul-Haq is solidly behind this one as he plays it back down the pitch.
Goes slightly fuller and angles the ball into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq displays his firm defense once again and blocks this back to the bowler.
Bowls this one outside the off stump on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq pushes this to the short cover fielder.
James Anderson bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends this with a straight bat towards silly mid on.
Goes really full and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique flicks the ball towards the short leg fielder. Ben Duckett gets his hands on the ball but had zero time to react and take the catch.
On a good length this time and in the off stump channel. Abdullah Shafique knocks this back towards the bowler.
Strays down leg side on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but the ball is far from his pads.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique dabs this towards point.
Maiden over for James Anderson and it has been a rarity in this game! He bowls this full as well and outside off, Abdullah Shafique strokes this towards mid on.
Ollie Robinson continues from 'round the wicket to the southpaw and serves this full outside off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this solidly to the off side.

FOUR! That has been punched away and it will be the first boundary for Pakistan! Ollie Robinson bowls this full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq knocks this past the fielder at mid on and the ball races away to the long on fence for four runs.
Ollie Robinson adjusts his length and goes short outside off, Imam-ul-Haq gets on top of the bounce and cuts the ball towards deep point. They complete three runs.
This is bowled back of a length and into the body of the batter. Abdullah Shafique tucks this towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Goes full and into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq flicks the ball towards the widish fine leg fielder and takes a run.
Full delivery bowled outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique defends this towards short cover and that will be LUNCH on Day 2!
Jack Leach begins with a full delivery outside the off stump, Imam-ul-Haq dabs it towards point.
Continues floating it full and just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this slightly short and into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq pushes this ball towards mid on.
Angled into the pads on a shorter length, Imam-ul-Haq uses the depth of the crease and flicks the ball towards square leg.
Bowls a straighter one full and outside the off stump, Imam-ul-Haq pushes at the ball but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Gets this closer to the stumps on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this to the left of the pitch.
Ollie Robinson starts off with a jaffa! Angles this into the batter from outside the off stump on a fuller length. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but gets beaten as the ball shapes away slightly.
