This is full as well and just outside off, Abdullah Shafique strokes this towards mid on. The fielder comes forward and stands at silly mid on now.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off, Ollie Robinson defends the ball towards short cover.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside the off pole, Abdullah Shafique blocks this solidly to short cover.

FOUR! That is a classical cover drive! Ollie Robinson goes full once again and serves this wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique gets a good stride forwards and strokes the ball to deep cover for a boundary.
Fast bowler's response from Ollie Robinson! Goes short outside off, Abdullah Shafique sways out of the way and leaves it alone.
Jack Leach flights this full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq pushes the ball towards cover.
Bowls this flatter on a fuller length just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq is looking solid in defense.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off pole, Imam-ul-Haq looks to hack this towards the leg side but mistime his shot to mid-wicket.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back down the pitch.
Delivers this wide outside off on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq taps this towards the silly mid off fielder.

Imam-ul-Haq had faced 11 dot balls off Jack Leach before this delivery! Jack Leach floats this one full and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq charges down the wicket and gets to the pitch of the ball. He lofts this over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Ollie Robinson bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique defends this towards short cover.
Angles this into the pads on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique clips this towards deep backward square leg and takes two runs.
In line with the stumps and on a good length, Abdullah Shafique defends this to the fielder at silly mid on.
Bowls a slower delivery on a good length and outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique waits on the ball and das it towards deep backward point to collect a couple of runs.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off pole, Abdullah Shafique taps this back towards the bowler.
Bowls this back of a length and towards the leg stump, Abdullah Shafique tucks the ball towards square leg to end the over with a dot ball.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq defends it off his front foot.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to square leg for none.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards Jack Leach.
Pulls his length back a bit, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it towards square leg.
Five dots now. Fuller and on middle and leg, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and defends it solidly.
Another maiden from Jack Leach. Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq stays firm and defends it to mid on.
Will Jacks starts with a fuller one on middle, Abdullah Shafique knocks it towards the fielder at mid off.
Flighted one on off, Abdullah Shafique eases it to short covers.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and slower one, Abdullah Shafique flicks it into the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary!
A low full toss and on off, Abdullah Shafique drives it to mid on. The ball hits him on the ankle while stopping it. Batters cross for a single.
Another fuller delivery, Imam-ul-Haq taps it to covers for one.
Slower one giving it air, Abdullah Shafique blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, this is defended well.
A quicker one on the pads, Imam clips it straight to the square leg fielder.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it through square leg as it races away for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to the short leg fielder.
Keeps it bowling fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq stands firm and blocks it away.
On off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards Will Jacks.
Slower one and on middle, Abdullah Shafique flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
Another dot as this is defended towards mid on.
Fuller and outside leg, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick it but misses. The keeper misses as they collect two byes.
Fuller one and on off, Abdullah Shafique eases it to mid on.
Fuller length around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Goes fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and defends it out.
Another fuller ball defended back towards Jack Leach.
FOUR! Finally opens up his blade. Fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq gets on his knee and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Slower and on off, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and blocks it away.
Fuller again, slower too. Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid off.
A quicker ball on the legs, Imam-ul-Haq tucks it away straight to the square leg fielder.

SIX! Up and over. Tossed up and on the stumps, Abdullah Shafique gets closer to the pitch and smokes it well over long on for a maximum! Brings up the 50 for Pakistan and the opening partnership is going strong so far.
Low full toss. Abdullah Shafique plays it down to mid on.
Fuller one as this is defended towards the square leg fielder.
Fuller again, this is blocked back towards Will Jacks.
Abdullah Shafique lunges and flicks the fuller ball to square leg for one.
Fuller one and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defeds it to short mid-wicket.
Quicker one on middle, Abdullah Shafique eases it back towards Jack Leach.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the bowler.
Tossed up, outside leg. Abdullah Shafique looks to flick it but gets his pads.
Bowls it full again, Abdullah Shafique eases it to mid on.
Steps down the track and Shafique plays the fuller ball back to Jack Leach.
Slower one this time, Abdullah Shafique blocks it out solidly.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq slaps it towards deep point for a brace.
Tighter line, keeps it straight. Imam-ul-Haq defends it towards mid on.
Fuller and slower through the air. Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid on again.
Tosses it up on middle, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it towards the short leg fielder.
Goes full, closer to the off stump. Another firm block by Imam-ul-Haq.
Fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to block it but gets his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Bowls it on middle, this is defended back towards Jack Leach.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique lofts it over mid on but doesn't get the power right. The fielder chases it. They collect two.
Outside off, this is played towards mid-wicket for one.
Quicker through the air. Fuller in length, this is defended off the front foot.
Fuller and quicker again, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to square leg for one.
Outside off by Jack Leach, left alone by Abdullah Shafique.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter one, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and smashes it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq prods and flicks to mid wicket.
Slower one on middle, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it and finds the fielder at point.
Slightly shorter one on off, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it to point for one.
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique drives it through covers for a boundary!
Quicker this time. Fuller in length, Abdullah Shafique drives it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Jack Leach fires this one into the stumps on a shortish length, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and defends this down the pitch.
Floats this one full and just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends this back towards the bowler.
Angles this into the pads on a shortish length, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and flicks the ball to the leg side.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off pole, Imam-ul-Haq is happy to block this back toward the bowler.
Continues to bowl full and keeps flighting this outside off. Imam-ul-Haq shimmies down the wicket and defends the ball back down the wicket.

Bowls this into the pads on a shorter length, Imam-ul-Haq uses the depth of the crease and tucks the ball towards deep square leg for three runs. Liam Livingstone runs behind the ball and collects it but he seems uncomfortable as it looks like he may have pulled some muscle.
Will Jacks bowls this full and into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq knocks this back towards the bowler.
Fires this one full and into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq clips the ball towards mid-wicket.
Floats one full outside the off stump, Imam-ul-Haq is not sure which way the ball is going to go and pushes at it. Gets an inside edge to deep backward square leg for a single.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique defends this solidly towards cover.
Bowls this quicker in the air and into the pads on a fuller length. Abdullah Shafique works this behind square of the leg side and gets a single.
Gives the ball more air this time and floats outside off on a fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq knocks this uppishly towards cover.
Flighted delivery bowled by Jack Leach full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends this back down the pitch.
Another loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique happy to block this towards silly mid off.

FOUR! This has been delicately played! Abdullah Shafique is expected the full delivery and he gets into position quickly. Abdullah Shafique paddles this from outside off and gets it to fine leg for four runs.
Flights this one as well and serves this outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends this towards cover.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique blocks this back to the bowler.
Angled into the stumps on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique shimmies down the wicket and dabs the ball towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Great use of his feet! Will Jacks floats one full and into the arc and Imam-ul-Haq charges down the wicket and hits this gun-barrel straight over the bowler's head for four runs.
This is full as well and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq goes back in the crease but the ball is not short and gets his bat down in time.
This is slightly short and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq punches this through point and takes a single.
Another full ball delivered outside off, Abdullah Shafique pushes this to covers.
Attacking the stumps this time and serves this full, Abdullah Shafique tucks this towards the legs side.
Looped on middle and on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Jack Leach keeps bowling full and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq defends the ball towards silly mid on.
This is full as well and just outside the off stump, Imam-ul-Haq knocks this towards cover.
Keeps bowling straight on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq defends this back towards the bowler.
Fourth dot ball in the over. Jack Leach keeps attacking the stumps and bowling full. Imam-ul-Haq smothers this into the pitch.
Angles this into the pads on a shorter length, Imam-ul-Haq tucks this to the leg side. Five dot balls now.
Another maiden over for Jack Leach! This is fired into leg stumps on a shorter length, Imam-ul-Haq clips this towards backward square leg.
Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller again, Abdullah Shafique rocks back and defends it away.
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Abdullah Shafique leans forward and drives it past covers for a boundary!
On off, fuller. This is defended towards square leg.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique looks to sweep it but misses. A loud appeal for stumping and the umpire goes upstairs to have a look. Replay shows that Abdullah Shafique was well in.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to covers.
Flatter and down leg, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to the short leg fielder.
Fuller one on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it solidly off the front foot.
Another fuller ball, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it back towards the bowler.
Full and on the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq plays it down to mid on for none.
Tossed up, straight on the middle. Imam-ul-Haq defends it to mid on.
Joe Root starts with a maiden. Full and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it back towards the bowler.
Slower through the air at a fuller in length, Abdullah Shafique pushes to covers.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique dances down the track and drives it past covers for a boundary!
Flighted up turning it away, Abdullah Shafique looks to block it but misses.
Outside off, Abdullah Shafique lets it go.
Fuller and slower one, Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Tosses it up on off, Abdullah Shafique gets on his knee and drives it past covers for a boundary. Fifty up for Abdullah Shafique. His fifth fifty in the Tests.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to the mid on fielder.
Quicker one and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards Joe Root.
Another fuller deliver, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to short leg.
FOUR! Excellent timing. Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq uses his feet and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Goes fuller, around off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it to covers for one. 100 up for Pakistan!
Slower one and on off. Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards he fielder at mid-wicket.
A single as Imam-ul-Haq flicks a fuller ball towards mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly.
Another one outside off, Abdullah Shafique eases it to mid off.
Will Jacks comes closer to the stumps and bowls it on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it back to him.
Tossed up, around off. Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly.
That is FIFTY for Imam-ul-Haq as well! Fifth test half-century for him too! Joe Root floats this one full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq dabs this towards cover and takes a single.
Joe Root bowls a bouncer! He bangs this in short and bowls this quick down leg side. Abdullah Shafique is surprised by the ball as it goes through to the keeper.
Goes full now into the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips the ball to mid-wicket.
Quicker on the legs, Abdullah Shafique tucks this to the leg side.
Strays further down leg side on a shortish length, Abdullah Shafique flicks this towards short fine leg.
Goes full and on a leg stump line, Abdullah Shafique clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
James Anderson starts the over with a full delivery angled into the stumps, Abdullah Shafique clips the ball to the square leg fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique blocks this towards the cover.
On a good length once again and well outside off, Abdullah Shafique dabs this to the right of point and takes a single.
Goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and serves this on a good length outside off. Imam-ul-Haq guides the ball to deep backward point and takes a couple of runs.
Bowls this fuller and angles this into the batter from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this solidly towards mid off.
On a good length this time and angled into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq defends this to the mid on fielder.
Joe Root flights this one full and well outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique blocks this towards cover.
Another delivery floated full and angled into the stumps. Abdullah Shafique defends this back to the bowler.
Fires this one full and way down leg side. Abdullah Shafique looks to sweep but misses. Ollie Pope does really well behind the wicket to collect the ball.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps, Abdullah Shafique pushes the back down the pitch toward the bowler.
Bowls this slightly short and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips this to the leg side.

Loopy delivery bowled full and just outside the off pole, Abdullah Shafique uses his wrists and flicks the ball past the short mid on fielder to collect two runs. The umpires have taken the bails off and that will be Tea on Day 2!
James Anderson starts from 'round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls this on a good length just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back down the pitch.
Strays onto the pads this time on a good length, Imam-ul-Haq tucks this to deep square leg and takes a single.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps, Abdullah Shafique clips this off his pads towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Full once again and attacking the stumps, Abdullah Shafique blocks this with a straight bat to the fielder at silly mid on.

That is a close call for Abdullah Shafique! James Anderson bangs this in short and angles the ball down leg side. Abdullah Shafique looks to fend this but gets a slight nick off the glove as it goes through to the keeper. Ollie Pope dives to his left and claims a fine catch. The umpires get together to discuss if the catch is taken cleanly and they go upstairs with the soft signal being Out. UltraEdge shows that there is a slight tremor when the ball passes the gloves but replays indicate the ball has bounced just before getting into the keeper's gloves. It will be NOT OUT and Pakistan at still no loss.
James Anderson bowls this full and into the stumps, Abdullah Shafique clips this towards mid-wicket.
Goes full on a leg stump line, Imam-ul-Haq flicks the ball towards deep square leg for a single.
Flights this one full and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips this towards deep mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs.
Looped up full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique blocks this towards cover.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off, Abdullah Shafique goes back into the crease and punches this towards extra cover.
Goes back to bowling full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique gets a stride forward and defends this to the cover fielder.

Jack Leach floats this one full and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique flicks the ball towards short leg where Keaton Jennings is placed. He gets hit directly on the stomach and it was hit too hard for him to get his hands around the ball.
On a length and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to short covers.
Good length again, on off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off this time, Imam-ul-Haq lets it go.
Fuller one and on off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly towards mid off.
Another one on off, Imam-ul-Haq knocks it to covers and scampers through for a single.
Fuller one and on middle, Abdullah Shafique eases it back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq defends it off his front foot.
FOUR! On off and slower one. Imam-ul-Haq dances down the track and drills it past the bowler and the umpire as the ball races away to the long off fence.
A quicker one on the pads, Imam-ul-Haq clips it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Another fuller ball defended towards mid-wicket.
Bowls it on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller length around off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it away back to the bowler.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Good length angling it in, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly.
Shorter one and on off, Abdullah Shafique guides it to backward point for a brace.
Another short ball, Abdullah Shafique pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
Fuller length angling in around off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it away to the mid off fielder.
Another dot ball as a fuller delivery is defended towards mid off.
Tossed up, on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique eases it to short covers for none.
Slower one and on middle, Abrar Ahmed gently flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
Fuller one, on off. This is defended back towards the bowler.
Another fuller delivery, Abdullah Shafique defends it towards the off side.
Bowls it outside off, Abdullah Shafique steers it towards point for one.
On a length and on middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it solidly.
Another length ball on leg, Abdullah Shafique eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to the fielder at silly mid on.
Good length angling it into the batter, Abdullah Shafique eases it to mid on.
On off, this is flicked towards square leg. Dot again.
On a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck. A maiden for James Anderson.
Fuller and on leg, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Slower one on middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
SIX! Up and over. Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique dances down the track and lofts it over long on and into the stands. Maximum!
Bowls it outside off, Abdullah Shafique cuts it to point for one.
Fuller and down leg, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and defends it well.
FOUR! Excellent timing on this. Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq smashes it over mid off for a boundary. Lovely shot from Imam-ul-Haq as Pakistan is turning it on here.
Bangs a shorter one on off, Abdullah Shafique fends it back towards the bowler.
Another shorter one on middle, Abdullah Shafique pulls it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Shorter again, on off. Abdullah Shafique ducks underneath it.
Bowls it shorter again, Abdullah Shafique pulls it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Shorter and on off, slower too. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it hard and through square leg for a boundary!
Shorter again, Imam-ul-Haq looks to pull it but misses.
FOUR! Pakistan are scoring freely now! Jack Leach serves this short and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique waits for the ball and cuts it late towards deep backward square leg for four runs.
Flights this one full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends this towards silly mid off.
Floats this one wide outside off on a fuller length, Abdullah Shafique pushes this to deep point and takes a single.
Bowls this slightly short and into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and punches this towards mid-wicket.
Sliding down leg side this time on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq misses his flick as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Goes full once again but this time outside the off stump, Imam-ul-Haq knocks this towards cover.
Ben Foakes bangs this in short and angling down leg, Abdullah Shafique initially looks to pull but decides against it.
Another short ball but well-directed this time. Abdullah Shafique ducks under the ball and lets it go through to the keeper.
Keeps bowling short and just outside the off stump, Abdullah Shafique sways out of the way this time. He is not being tempted into the pull shot so far.
Finally goes for it! Ben Stokes bowls this back of a length and into the batter. The ball does not rise much and Abdullah Shafique pulls it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Continue bowling short to the left-hander as well and just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq pulls this into the deep mid-wicket region and takes a run.
On a good length this time and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique tucks this towards backward square leg. Dot ball to end the over.
Jack Leach fires this one full and into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq clips this towards square leg.
Bowls this slightly short and into the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq works this towards deep mid-wicket and takes a run.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside off, Abdullah Shafique pushes this towards cover and takes one.
Floats this one full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends this back towards the bowler.
Short once again and into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq goes on his backfoot and taps the ball towards mid-wicket.
Continues bowling short and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq defends with a straight bat towards silly mid on.

Ben Stokes bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump. Abdullah Shafique gets on his toes and punches the ball in the gap towards deep point. They will take three runs as the fielder chases and collects the ball.
Bangs this in short and in line with the stumps. The ball does not bounce much and Imam-ul-Haq pulls this into the square leg region for a single.
Continues bowling back of a length and outside off, Abdullah Shafique stands tall and fends this into the off side.
Ben Stokes decides to bowl full now and attacks the stumps, Abdullah Shafique blocks this towards short mid on.

FOUR! Easy pickings for Abdullah Shafique and he plays this wonderfully well! Ben Stokes goes back to bowling short but angles this down leg. Abdullah Shafique has all the time in the world to help it down to fine leg for four runs.
Decides to bowl this one a good length and into the pads. Abdullah Shafique clips the ball towards square leg.
Jack Leach floats this one full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back down the pitch.
Bowls this flatter and into the stumps on a fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq shimmies down the wicket and defends solidly.

FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq is picking his shots here and getting well rewarded for his patience! This is flighted full and just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq charges down the wicket and thumps the ball over the in-field towards long on for a boundary.
Goes full once again and in line with the stumps. Shimmies forward again but decides to defend it.
FOUR! This has been powered away! Jack Leach goes full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq stays back in the crease and thumps the ball towards long off for four more runs.
Bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq defends this off the back foot and keeps the ball out.
Flighted delivery bowled full and just outside off, Abdullah Shafique knocks this towards mid off and takes a quick single.

FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq looks deceived in the air but still manages to get a boundary! Will Jacks floats this wide outside off on a fuller length, Imam-ul-Haq charges down the wicket and slices the ball towards deep cover for four runs.
Fires this one full and into the pads, Imam-ul-Haq clips the ball to wide mid on and takes a single.
Goes full and in line with the stumps, Abdullah Shafique blocks this back down the pitch to the bowler.
Flighted full and into the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips this toward mid-wicket.
Another loopy delivery bowled full and just outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends this solidly with a straight bat.
Flights this one full and straight, Imam-ul-Haq shimmies down the wicket and defends the ball down the wicket.
Another fuller one, Imam-ul-Haq hangs back and defends it from his crease.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the bowler.
FOUR! Bowls it on off, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and smashes it through mid off for a boundary!
Goes fuller on the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq defends it solidly.
Keeps it fuller once again. Imam-ul-Haq lunges and defends it firmly once again.
Fuller and angling away from the batter. Abdullah Shafique lunges and drives it straight to covers.
Abdullah Shafique skips down and flicks the length ball towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, this is played towards mid off.
Flighted, outside the off. Abdullah Shafique strides and plays it down to mid off.
On off, this is defended off the front foot.
Goes fuller again, Abdullah Shafique flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Full and straight. Imam-ul-Haq strides and defends it off the front foot.
Quicker and on off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and defends it out.
Fuller and arround off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid on.
Bowls it down leg, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards square leg for a brace.
Tossed up, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly.
Full on the middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq is happy to block this one out as well. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Woah! That was a surprise. Root starts off with a bumper. Shafique ducks under it.
On off, defended.
Slower through the air and on middle, defended.
On the stumps, this is pushed back to the bowler.
On the stumps, kept out.
First run of the day! On middle, this is worked to mid on for one.
Very full and on middle, this is played back to the bowler.
On off, kept out.
Confusion but safe! On middle, this is pushed towards mid On. Anderson dives over the ball. They take two. Shafique wants the third and sets off. He is sent back but in time.
On off, kept out.
Fires it on off, blocked.
Shortish and outside off, this is guided to point.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
On middle, kept out.
On the stumps again, this us pushed to mid off.
Slightly fuller and on off, this is pushed to cover.
Fires it on middle, kept out.
Nicely played for two more! Outside off, Imam guides it past short third man and takes two.
On middle, kept out.
Well played in the end! Steps out but does not get to the pitch of it, he pushes it to mid off and takes one.
On off, kept out.
Sees Imam come down the track and shortens the length. Defended.
Imam uses his feet again but does not get to the pitch of the ball, he works It to mid on.
Tidy from Leach! On middle, this is flicked to mid on.
On middle, this is played back to the bowler.
On the stumps, defended.
Kept out again as this is floated up on middle.
SIX! BANG! That goes over the fence. He moves onto 99! This time he gets t the pitch of it and heaves it over the mid-wicket fence. Has two balls to get to his ton in this over.

Gets it on the next ball itself! Another ton for Abdullah Shafique! His third in 8 Tests. He is having a lovely time in this format. Has impressed right from the time he has made his debut. He can make a big one here. Gets there by dabbing this flatter ball towards point and takes one.
On off, kept out.
On middle, slightly slower, little bit of turn but kept out well.
Slightly shorter this time, Abdullah Shafique pushes it wide of mid off and takes one.
On middle, Imam works it to mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked.
Pushes this one though but Imam goes quickly onto the back foot and works it to mid-wicket.
Another dot! Imam remains in the 90s! On middle, Imam flicks it to mid-wicket.
Close! This lands on middle and then spins in. Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but it goes past the inside edge and to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to covers.
FOUR! 200 up for Pakistan! On the pads, this is swept hard and fine on the leg side for a boundary.
On the stumps, kept out.
On the stumps again, blocked.
Imam is just a boundary away now! Shorter and around off, Imam guides it past point and takes two.
On middle, defended.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to cover.
On middle, Imam flicks it to mid-wicket.

Not the best of calls but a single in the end! On off, this is pushed towards mid off. Imam waits initially and then goes for the single. Abdullah Shafique is late to take off but makes it in the end. The throw too was not the best from the fielder.
Leading edge but safe! On middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to work it on the leg side but closes the face of the bat early, it goes off the leading edge but wide of the bowler.
On middle, kept out.
In the air again but shor! On middle, Imam works it uppishly but lands short of Root who dives and stops it to his left.
Making it difficult for Imam to get to his ton! Yet again on middle, this is pushed to cover.
Fires it on off, Imam defends it.
Fuller and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
Good stuff from Root! On middle, Imam plays it back to the bowler. Good from him too, he is taking his time and not rushing to get to the ton.
On off, Abdullah Shafique is solid in defense.
Yet again, this is floated up on off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it.
On the stumps, Abdullah Shafique defends it back towards the bowler.
Loopy ball on off, Abdullah Shafique pushes it to cover.
5 dots in a row! On off, flighted ball, Abdullah Shafique defends it onto the ground.
It is a maiden! On the stumps, this is played to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, Imam plays it back to the bowler.
Fires it on middle, Imam lunges and keeps it out.
Fuller and on off, this is pushed to cover.
Just over! Imam's patience runs out. He steps out, does not get to the pitch of it but goes ahead with the shot. It goes more off the outer half over cover and takes two. Lucky escape. He gets to 99.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.

FOUR! This time he gets it past mid on and gets to his ton in style! Just like the English openers, both the Pakistan openers get hundreds too. He just loves batting at this venue. Another ton for him here and this will make him feel really good. He was stuck for a pretty long time in the nervous 90s and now he has got to his ton. Gets a full ball on the pads which he flicks past mid on and it races away to the fence.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Steps out, makes room and then lifts it over cover, goes inside-out and bags a boundary. Tough shot but played really well.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up on off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it.
On the stumps, this is pushed to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Abdullah Shafique defends.
On the stumps, defended.
Two more! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
On middle, Imam pushes it to cover.
Fuller and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
Attacks the stumps again, Root is pushing it through, Imam plays it onto the ground.
FOUR! Put away! Root looks to surprise the batter by bowling another bumper but Imam rocks back and hammers it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A dot to end! On middle, Imam-ul-Haq leans forward and keeps it out.
Angled into the pads, Abdullah Shafique works it wide of mid on for one.
Flatter and on off, Imam pushes it to silly mid on.
Flighted ball on off, Imam defends.
On middle, this is worked to short leg.
Floats it up on off, Imam keeps it out.
A dot to end! On middle, defended.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique goes back and guides it past point for a boundary.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, defended.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Stop the press, England finally manage to find the opening wicket. The move to get Will Jacks on works. HE GETS HIS FIRST TEST WICKET! Not the best of balls. It is short and wide outside off. Abdullah Shafique looks to cut but he tries to play it really late. It goes off the outside edge and it is taken by the keeper. Pope just about takes it. A good catch in the end as it was a thick edge. A superb knock from Abdullah Shafique but he had a chance to make a daddy ton here.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Will Jacks

Commentary: On off, defended.
That has hit the pad outside off! This lands outside off and turns back in. Azhar Ali looks to flick by getting outside the line of off. He misses to get hit on the pads. Turned down.
SIX! BANG! A wicket has fallen but Imam does not care! He steps out and lofts it over the long on fence for a biggie.
On middle, defended.
Sharp turn! This is tossed up outside off, Imam gets his front pad outside the line and looks to defend, it hits the pad and lobs on the off side.

He lofts it down the ground but hits it quite flat. It goes towards long on where it is taken by Ollie Robinson! Pakistan still a long way away, England will sense an opening here. They still lead by over 400.
Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Jack Leach

THE FINGER IS RAISED! Azhar Ali has been given out LBW but he reviews. Seems no bat but is it going down leg or is it clipping the leg pole? OUT! None of the two mentioned above, IT IS HITTING THE LEG POLE! THREE REDS! The second new ball has done the trick and England have their third in the session. This is a big wicket. Leach bowls it quicker and slightly shorter on middle, Azhar Ali goes back to flick but since, the ball is new, it skids through. Ali is late in getting his bat down and is hit on the pads. An appeal and the finger goes up. Can England take another one before Lunch? Pakistan still trail by over 350.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

He has also got this ton up in no time. Gets there in style again. Short and outside off, he slaps it through covers for a boundary.

Ollie Robinson continues to angle it across, outside off. Shakeel is drawn forward to drive but he gets an outside edge to Ollie Pope who makes no mistake. The 123-run stand is broken. England have an opening and they need to build on this.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Ollie Robinson

OUT! BABAR AZAM GOES! End of a fine innings from the Pakistani skipper. Azam walks back in disappointment. Will Jacks is happy and so are England. He serves a shorter ball, outside off, there is turn and extra bounce. Azam goes back to cut but gets an outside edge to point. Jack Leach takes it safely. Babar Azam will feel he has given away his wicket. Was batting so nicely. Missed out on his 150.
Howout: c Jack Leach b Will Jacks

He serves it from 'round the wicket, touch fuller and on middle. Rizwan flicks n the up and straight in the hands of Ben Stokes who takes a sharp catch at short mid-wicket. England are in ecstasy. They can feel they can bundle out Pakistan till the end of the day.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b James Anderson

Flatter and outside off, dabbed to third man for one. Mahmood to keep the strike.
Full and outside off. Mahmood leans and knocks it to point.
This one spins in, on off. Defended on the front foot.
Tossed up on middle. Mahmood steps across to block.
Flatter and on middle. Mahmood tries to defend but inside edges it on the deck.
Very full and on off. Kept out.
Goes very full and on leg. Mahmood blocks it out.
A leading edge to begin with! Fuller and on the pads, Salman looks to flick, closes the face of the bat early, it goes off a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
First runs of the day! Fuller and on the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Fires it on middle, Zahid Mahmood keeps it out.
Negotiates the last ball well! On the stumps, Zahid gets right behind the line and defends.
Good shot for no runs! This shot just shows the wicket is still good to bat on! Length and on off, Salman strokes it on the up to covers.
Another one on a length and around off, defended.
Length and on off, this one shapes away a touch. Agha guides it through point. Turns down the run.
This time Salman does take the single with two balls to go! Length and on off, this is guided through point.
A little too straight from Anderson! Zahid works it to mid-wicket.
A single turned down on the last ball! On the pads, this is clipped towards fine leg. Agha Salman does not take one as he wants strike.
FOUR! That is swept brilliantly! On middle, Salman goes down on one knee and hits it through square leg for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, Salman pushes it to covers.
A little bit of turn there! Shorter and outside off, this lands and spins away. Salman looks to cut but is beaten. Looks at the pitch immediately.
On middle, defended.

SIX! This is good batting! Stokes had got the field up to stop the single and Salman takes the opportunity to go big. Steps out, gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over the long on fence for a biggie.

FOUR! 10 from the final two balls and 14 from the over. England though will get to bowl to Zahid Mahmood at the start of the next over. Salman uses his feet again but Leach shortens the length. He manages to whip it past mid on and it races away to the fence.
Some swing back in for Anderson! On the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.

FOUR BYES! Handy runs for Pakistan! Anderson who is looking to bowl quite straight errs in line and bowls it well down the leg side. It swings away from Pope who dives but fails to stop it. It goes down to the fine leg fence. Runs coming thick and fast for the hosts.
Good length and on off, defended.
FOUR! That is nicely played! Shorter in length and outside off, Zahid Mahmood rides on top of the bounce and guides it down to third man. No fielder there and a boundary results.
Solid! Length and on off, defended.
A yorker then to end, it comes back in from outside off. Zahid Mahmood jams it out well.

NOT OUT! Salman is in! This is tossed up outsde off, it lands and turns away. Salman looks to go over covers but is beaten. The keeper whips the bails off and appeals. It is taken upstairs. They check Ultra Edge first and it shows a flat line. Then the stumping which is also safe as Salman is in.
Tossed up on off, Salman blocks.
A single as this is guided with the turn through point.
On middle, blocked.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.

Good from Zahid Mahmood! On off, kept out.

FOUR! That was almost brilliant from Root! Jacks goes around the wicket and fires this full and outside off. Salman plays the reverse sweep. Root at first slip starts moving to his right as he sees Salman play the shot. He then dives to his right and sticks one hand out, it does hit the hand but does not stay in. It goes down to the third man fence. It would have been something magical had he taken it.

NOT OUT! It has indeed pitched outside leg! On the pads, Salman looks to sweep but is through the shot as the ball holds in the surface. He misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal and after giving it a long thought, the umpire raises the finger. Salman reviews and replays show that the on-field call has to be overturned.
On middle, defended.
On off, kept out.
On the stumps, blocked well.

FLoats it up on off, blocked.
Two more! Outside off, this is carved past point for two.

Zahid Mahmood would have been gone by a long way! Not sure if such a risky run needed to be taken! On off, this is guided towards the off side and they go for one. Pope goes for the ball, picks it up and as he turns, has a shy at his end but misses. Zahid was gone.

FOUR BYES! Useful runs for Pakistan whereas, this is frustrating for England. Fifty-run stand up between the two. Crucial one. This is tossed up outside off. Salman looks to sweep but misses. It goes past the keeper and down to the third man fence.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
On the stumps, defended.
On off, Salman manages to push it to cover.
FOUR! That is a top shot! This is tossed up slightly. Agha Salman stays leg side and just lofts it nonchalantly over the cover fielder and it goes for a boundary.
Now takes one and keeps strike as he pushes it to the left of mid off.
On off, defended.
On middle, kept out.
Flatter and on middle, it is kept out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The last recognized batter for Pakistan falls shortly after getting to his half ton! Jacks has his fourth. Really well bowled. This lands on off and then goes on with the angle. Agha Salman stays back and looks to defend but this goes off the outside edge and Root at first slip takes a sharp catch. A good little innings from Salman but he needed to continue. England still lead by over 100. Can England now make quick work of the remaining wickets?
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Will Jacks

Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards mid off for a quick run. Haris Rauf was struggling as he completed that run.

OUT! STUMPED! Probably the right call in the end! Zahid Mahmood did not look like having anything behind the line. Time to celebrate for Will Jacks as he gets a FIFER ON DEBUT! The long resistance of Zahid Mahmood comes to an end! He tries to innovate. Brings out the reverse sweep but this is fired outside off. He misses. Pope whips the bails off and appeals. It is taken upstairs. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Time to check the stumping. The umpire saw a few replays and then decided the foot was on the line. Pakistan 9 down and still behind by 81 runs.
Howout: st Ollie Pope b Will Jacks

Commentary: On middle, kept out.
Shorter and around off, Rauf really looks to hit it hard but misses.
Good shot! Fuller and on off, this is pushed through covers for two.
Goes short and on the body, Rauf looks to pull, it goes off the splice and lobs over Keaton Jennings at short leg. One taken.
Half an appeal but turned down! Short and on the body, Ali looks to fend it but it hits the body and lobs towards short leg.
That has hit the batter! Short and on the body again, Ali looks to fend it away but misses to get hit on the body.
On off, defended.

OUT! TAKEN! Six-fer for Will Jacks! Another good catch by Root! Rauf steps out, Jacks tosses it up outside off. Rauf swings, this goes off the outside edge and Root takes it at first slip. Pakistan have been bowled out for 579!
Howout: c Joe Root b Will Jacks

Commentary: Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one. England are underway along with Crawley.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Pakistan strike on the second ball! A ton for Ben Duckett in the first innings and a duck in the second. Not a shot he will be proud of. He could have left that alone. This is on a length and outside off, Duckett goes after it, this goes off the outside edge to second slip and it is taken Agha Salman. That is the perfect start for the hosts.
Howout: c Agha Salman b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Angled into the pads, Pope looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. A run taken. Leg bye.
On off, defended.

A loud shot but going down! On the pads, Zak Crawley looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down. Azam indicates there was an inside edge and he was right as Ultra Edge shows a spike as the ball passes the bat.

OUT! TAKEN! Pope has been bounced out and Pakistan have another one. England are effectively 114 for 2. A short one and on middle, Pope goes for the pull, he fails to get on top of the bounce, it goes off the top edge towards fine leg and it is taken easily by Shah. Another centurion from the first innings walks back for a low score. Can Pakistan get another one before the break?
Howout: c Naseem Shah b Mohammad Ali

Just over the fielder! A brilliant dipping slower ball, it is a full toss but a dipping one. Zak Crawley was completely done in by the lack of pace. He ends up chipping it but over the leaping fielder at mid off for two.

Around off, Zak Crawley pushes it through covers for one.

On off, this is pushed through cover for one.

A LOUD APPEAL FOR CAUGHT BUT TURNED DOWN! Rizwan wants it to be reviewed and it is. Crawley indicates it has hit his shoulder. OUT! There is a spike on Ultra Edge as it passes the glove and the on-field call has to be overturned! Not sure why Crawley was rubbing his shoulder as that was nowhere near the shoulder. He falls shortly after getting to his half ton. Down the leg side, short. Crawley looks to pull, this seems to have taken the glove and Rizwan takes it. A successful review from Pakistan and a much-needed wicket as this stand was taking the game away from them.
Howout: c Mohammad Rizwan b Mohammad Ali

DROPPED! Not an easy chance though! Root plays the switch hit. He drags it from outside leg and towards cover. The fielder dives to his left, gets two hands to it but can't hang on. A run taken.
Shorter and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one.
FOUR! The reverse sweep and this time he gets the desired result! A full toss on the pads, Root plays the reverse sweep down to the third man fence.

OUT! TAKEN! The crowd finds its voice now! Something for them to be happy about as it was all England in this session. On the pads, Root looks to sweep but fails to get on top of the bounce. It goes off the top edge and Imam-ul-Haq takes an easy catch at short fine leg. A good innings from Root comes to an end. England effectively 270 for 4.

Commentary: On middle, kept out. Stokes wants a sighter.
Out comes the reverse sweep but Stokes finds point.

OUT! TAKEN! Really not sure what Stokes was trying to do there! It all looked ugly in the end! This is slower and it lands around off and it is turning back in. Stokes looks to hit it through covers. The length and line was not the right one to play that shot. This takes the top edge as Stokes fails to get on top of the bounce and lobs upto cover where Saud takes it. Two in quick succession for Zahid and Pakistan.
Howout: c Saud Shakeel b Zahid Mahmood

Fifty for Brook! What a debut he is having! A 150 followed by a half ton and he is not done yet! Gets there by working it through mid-wicket for one.

That was quite slow from Brook! Not sure what he was thinking about. He steps out but does not get to the pitch of it. Defends it and then stands his ground. Rizwan is quick to the ball and looks to back flick it onto the stumps. Brook realises and looks to make it back in. Rizwan misses his shy.
SIX! Right in the arc and out of the park! This is given a lot of air and it is very full. It is heaved over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
