Shorter and around off, this is guided through point for one.
Short and on middle, Liam looks to pull, he gets an inside edge onto the pads. It rolls on the off side. A run taken.

OUT! TIMBER! No consecutive tons for Brook but yet another wonderful innings from him and a debut to remember. Maybe he could have played his way to his ton but that shot just shows, it is team first for him. On middle, he looks to heave it across the line but misses it altogether. The stumps are shattered. Brook walks back and so do the umpires and the players as THAT IS TEA ON DAY 4!
Howout: b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Goes fuller and on off, no swing on offer, Abdullah Shafique strokes it to mid off.
Another one on a good length, no movement again. Defended.
Now goes short, realises there is no movement and bangs it short. Left alone.
Another short one and on middle, Abdullah Shafique does not fiddle with it. A no ball though as Ollie Robinson oversteps.
Goes short again, outside off, Abdullah Shafique looks to pull but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Bangs it short again and on middle, Abdullah Shafique ducks under it.
FOUR! Short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique pulls, it goes to the deep square leg fence. First boundary of the chase and a good first over for Pakistan.
FOUR! Hammered! That has been thumped! A short ball and it sits up to be hit. Imam slams it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Off the mark in style.
FOUR! Cut away! That was asking to be hit! It is short and outside off, Imam cuts it through point and it races away to the fence. Pakistan off to a flier.
A bumper now, Imam ducks under it.
A real effort ball, gets good bounce and also good zip off this slow surface. Imam ducks under it.
Good length and on off, Imam defends it towards cover.
Another short one on the body, Imam lets it go over him.
Shorter and on middle, this is blocked.
On the shorter side again, Abdullah Shafique nudges it on the leg side.
On the shorter side, Abdullah Shafique lets it go to the keeper again.
Around off, Abdullah Shafique looks to pull this time but misses. He is beaten by the pace.
Outside off, this is guided down to third man for one.
Back of a length and on off, defended. No ball signaled as Ollie Robinson oversteps. It is a huge no ball.
Another short one, Imam does not fiddle with it.
Short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique pulls it through mid-wicket and takes one.
Another short one, Imam lets it go over him.
FOUR! Thumped down the ground! Goes short and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq pulls, he manages to pull it past mid on for a boundary.
Short and outside off, Imam lets it go.
Another one on the shorter side. Left alone.
Bangs it short and on middle, Imam defends it.

OUT! TAKEN! Abdullah Shafique holes out! The plan to bowl short has worked. Early wicket for England. Just what they needed! This is banged in short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique can't hold back, he goes for the pull, fails to get on top of the bounce and it goes off the top edge towards deep square leg. Harry Brook at deep square leg takes it nicely.
Howout: c Harry Brook b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Back of a length and on off, Ali defends.
Another short one on middle, Ali looks to fend it but is hit on the glove.
Short and on middle, this is defended.
FOUR! Slammed away! This is short and asking to be hit! Azam waits and slaps it through covers for a boundary. First for Azam and he is underway.
Another bumper, Azam lets it go over him. A successful over then for Ollie Robinson!
Outside off, Imam-ul-Haq guides it down to third man for one.
Bangs it in short and on off, Babar Azam defends it onto the ground.

OUT! TAKEN! The finger is raised! Pin-drop silence in this stadium as Babar Azam has been dismissed by the England skiper, Ben Stokes. The short ball ploy works yet again. England well and truly on top now! This is short and on middle, Babar Azam looks to guide it down to third man. There is not enough room to do that. He actually tried making a little bit of room by moving to his the right. This goes off the toe-end and it is taken inches above the ground by the keeper. Two out of the three centurions from the first innings for Pakistan are back in the hut. Do Pakistan have another hero in them?
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Back of a length and on off, Saud defends it.
Another short one and on middle, Saud ducks under it.
Yet another short one, Saud ducks under it.
Shorter and on middle, Imam pulls but to mid-wicket.
On the shorter side, this is defended.
Another one on the shorter side, fended.
This time Imam does find the gap with the pull, he plays it towards deep square leg only for one.
Down the leg side, Saud leaves it alone.
Bangs it short from around the wicket, defended.
Another one on the shorter side, Imam hops and defends it.
On the body, Imam nudges it on the leg side and takes one.

FOUR! Flayed away! Slightly shorter and outside off, Saud cuts it past point for a boundary. He played a similar shot to the one he got out in the first innings but this time the length was shorter and hence, he was able to get it away.
Another short one, Shakeel lets it go over him.
Another one on the shorter side, this is pulled towards square leg for one.
Stokes goes short to end the over, Imam ducks under it.
Another no ball! Outside off, left alone.
On the shorter side, this is nudged on the leg side for one.
Back of a length and on middle, Imam defends it onto the ground.
FOUR! Gets hold of this one, really well! Short and on middle, Imam pulls it hard, it races through backward square leg and into the fence.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Really good pull shot again! This is on the body, Imam is getting on top of the bounce nicely and hammers it through square leg. Another boundary for him.
Yet again gets on top of this short ball and pulls it onto the ground but to mid-wicket.
On the shorter side, Suad pulls but finds square leg.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes short, Saud lets it go over him.
Digs it in halfway down the wicket, Saud is happy to evade it.
Another duck as yet again Anderson goes short and on the body.
Continues to bang it short and the batter continues to duck under it.
Imam straightaway gives Leach the charge but does not get to the pitch of it. Imam defends it.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Gives it air and lands it on off, kept out.
On the stumps, kept out.
Loopy ball on off, blocked.
On the shorter side, defended.
Another short ball on the body, evaded.
Bangs it short, Saud stands tall and defends.
Continues to bowl the shorter length. Saud lets it go to the keeper. Saud is not interested in taking on the bumper. Maybe England can sneak in a full one here to surprise Shakeel.
Another short one and on the body, Saud yet again ducks under it.
FOUR! This time nails the pull shot! Times it brilliantly! Short and on the body, this is pulled brilliantly through square leg. No chance for the fielder in the deep.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
On off, defended.
On middle, this is worked to mid on for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Tossed up on middle, Saud lifts it over silly mid on for a boundary. Smart short, there was no mid on in place and he just chipped it over the fielder close-in.
On middle, defended.
FOUR! Smart stuff yet again! Uses his feet but does not get to the pitch of it. Still chips it over the silly mid on fielder for another boundary.
Three more! Runs flowing now! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for three.
Tossed up outside off, slower, left alone.
FOUR! Cut away! This is short and outside off, Saud cuts it past point for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, defended.
Slower and outside off, Saud lets it be.
On the stumps, blocked.
Imam steps down the track but does not get to the pitch of it. Defends.
Two more! Shorter and outside off, this one turns back in. Imam-ul-Haq still manages to cut towards point for two.
FOUR! Cut away! Another one short and outside off, this time there is enough width on offer and Imam cashes in. He cuts it past point for a boundary.
Flatter and on off, defended.
On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, Shakeel blocks.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
FOUR! Imam steps out and gets to the pitch of it, lofts it clean and over the mid off fielder for another boundary.
On middle, defended.
On off, defended.
Shortish and on off, this is played to point.
On the shorter side, this is guided to point for one.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Flatter and on off, kept out.
On off, this is worked down to long on with the turn for one.
On the stumps, Saud gets right behind the line and defends.
On off, blocked.
Two! On the pads, this is worked towards fine leg for a couple.
Misreads the length there! Flatter and on the pads, Imam looks to stay back to a relatively full ball, gets his bat down in time and works it to square leg.
Steps out now and almost yorks himself, jams it out towards cover.
Floats it up on off, Imam defends.
Another one on middle, blocked.
On middle, kept out.
Chance? Half a chance! On middle, Saud works it firmly towards short leg. It hits his hand but does not stay in. Needed to react very quickly.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
On the stumps, blocked.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Two more! On the shorter side, this is pushed through covers for two.
On the stumps, kept out.
That was very well bowled! Imam steps out, Root shortens the length and also slows it. The ball turns a little too. Imam defends it.
Slower through the air again and outside off, left alone.
On off, this is guided towards point for one.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Another one tossed up on off, Saud plays it to cover.
Beauty to start with! A length ball, angling outside off before it nips away. Imam prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Pakistan are off the mark on Day 5! Length ball, outside off. Imam lunges forward, slices it past backward point for a boundary.
Extra bounce this time! Short in length, on middle. Imam stays back to defend, mistimes it to square leg.
A loud shout but mainly from behind! Short and outside off, extra bounce again. Imam pushes forward to defend but misses.
On middle, blocked out.
Length ball, outside off. Imam pushes it to cover.
A length ball, outside off, knocked to cover.

FOUR! Through the gap for four! Length ball, outside off. Shakeel punches off the back foot through covers. Zak Crawley gives a chase, does all the hard work but fails to flick it perfectly and the ball rolls back and touches the ropes.
On middle, blocked out.
Goes full, outside off, it is driven to cover.
Angles a full ball on middle, it's driven to mid off.
BEATEN! On a length and outside off, holds its line. Shakeel looks to defend but misses.
Length and on off. Imam taps it to point.
Length ball on middle. Imam clips it past square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Shakeel keeps it out.
Length ball, outside off. Shakeel shoulders arms to it.
This is outside off again, it is left alone.
Way outside off. Shakeel lets it go to the keeper.
Short of a length and on middle, nudged to square leg.
Angling down the leg side. Imam misses his flick.
On a length and on middle. Imam gets his bat in front to defend.
Length and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Slants a length ball on middle. Imam stays back and defends it out.
A maiden for James! On a length and on middle. Imam watchfully blocks it out.
On middle, kept out.
This is full and outside off. Shakeel pushes  it to cover.
Another dot as Shakeel works it to cover.
Ollie Robinson bowls from 'round the wicket and serves it around off. Shakeel has his stumps covered as he blocks it.
On a length and slanting on off. Defended on the deck.
A maiden for Robinson as well! This is full and angling on middle. Shakeel tries to work on the leg side but mistimes it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.
On middle, length and it is blocked it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Imam-ul-Haq goes and England have found the breakthrough. The 64-run stand is broken. Imam could have left this alone. James Anderson slants a length ball, going down the leg side. Imam tries to flick it but gets a faint edge to Ollie Pope who dives to his right and takes a fine catch. First, it looked like it came off the pads but Imam-ul-Haq showed his back immediately and started walking off. He goes for fine 48.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b James Anderson

Commentary: On a length and on middle. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off at 128 clicks. Rizwan pokes it to point.
On the pads, pushed to mid-wicket.
A bouncer, outside off. Shakeel lets it go.
This is close to the body but Shakeel makes a good leave.
Short in length and on middle. Shakeel pulls it to square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle. Blocked out.
Length and on off. Defended out.
James Anderson keeps the same channel, angling across on middle. Shakeel blocks it out.
James Anderson slants one outside off. Shakeel watchfully lets it go.
Shakeel has shown a good defensive show. On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and outside off. Shakeel drives it to cover.
Very full now on middle, it's flicked to mid-wicket.
On drive comes out. Full and on middle, this is hit to mid on.
Very full and on middle. Blocked out.
On off, kept out.
This is full and outside off, pushed to cover.
Very full and on off. Mohammad Rizwan leans and drives it straight to mid off.
A length ball, outside off. Mohammad Rizwan is early as he looks to drive, mistimes it to mid-wicket.
Length and on off. Mohammad Rizwan prods and defends it out.
Outside off, knocked to cover.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
Short in length on middle. Shakeel tucks it to square leg. Since nothing is happening, it looks like a change is imminent by Ben Stokes.
Shorter and outside off. Shakeel leaves it alone.
Tails a full ball on the pads, it is hit to mid-wicket.
Pitches it up, outside off. Shakeel drives it to mid off and takes a quick single. The fielder hits the stumps at the bowler's end but Shakeel was in.
Angles a length ball, outside off. Shakeel shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, outside off. Shakeel leaves it alone.
Another leave! On a length and outside off. Shakeel watches it go.
Length and on off, kept out.
On a length and around off. Shakeel is drawn forward as he knocks it to cover.
That was not far away! On a length and outside off. Shakeel pushes it firmly, gets an outside edge past Zak Crawley who is standing much closer than normal at the short third man region. One.
Outside off, left alone.
Short of a length and outside off. Shakeel hops and works it to point.
This is full and on middle, Saud eases it to mid on.
On a length and on off. Shakeel keeps it out.
This is angled outside off. Shakeel leaves it alone for the keeper.
Short in length and on off. Shakeel punches off the back foot to cover.
Ben Stokes still wants to go with these two. Nothing off the pitch for the bowlers. On off, left alone.
This is full and outside off. Mohammad Rizwan reaches and drives it to cover.
Tight from Ollie Robinson. On middle, blocked out.
Pakistan look like they want to go to Lunch unhurt. Short and outside off. Mohammad Rizwan shoulders arms to it.

Leg bye! The English players get together as they think to review it but it looed like going down and Ollie Pope suggests the same. Ben Stokes listens to his keeper and walks away. Yes, the replay confirms it is going down. This is full and tailing on the pads, going more away. Mohammad Rizwan misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Full and outside off, pushed to cover.
Tossed up on middle. Defended on the front foot.
Fuller and on off. Mohammad Rizwan leans and blocks again.
On middle, defended out.
Flatter and outside off. Rizwan punches it straight to cover.
Tossed up on middle. Mohammad Rizwan shows a full bat to block out.
Tossed up on middle. Defended out again. A maiden to start for Leach.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for one.
FOUR! Mohammad Rizwan opens his account! Flighted, outside off. Rizwan slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Not off the middle but enough to go over the man.
Flatter and on middle. Mohammad Rizwan rocks back and defends.
FOUR! Looks like the message has been received to score more often now. Tossed up on off. Mohammad Rizwan skips down and heaves it to deep mid-wicket for four more.
This one lands on middle and turns away. Rizwan opens his body as he looks to pull but gets an inside edge to fine leg for one.
13 off the over! On the pads, flicked through square leg for one.
Very full, outside off, pushed to mid off for one.
On middle, blocked out.
Full and outside off. Rizwan drives it to cover.
This one lands outside off and spins away. Rizwan is drawn forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Something for the spinners there.
FOUR! Good shot! Shorter and outside off. Rizwan slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Hitting the loose balls away. Down the leg side, swept behind square leg for a couple.
Down the leg side. Saud Shakeel leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off. Saud Shakeel knocks it to cover for a single.
Full and outside off, defended on the front foot.
Floated full and outside off. Rizwan sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Defended out.
On the pads, this is flicked past mid-wicket for easy couple.
Flatter and on middle. Rizwan works it to the off side.
Full and on off. Blocked on the front foot.
On middle. Rizwan prods to defend.
On middle, it is driven to mid on.
Another dot! Flatter and on middle, kept out.
A maiden for Leach. Flatter and on off. Rizwan rocks back and dead bats it.
Shorter and outside off. Saud Shakeel punches it to cover for a quick single.
Shorter and down leg, pulled straight to short fine leg.
Flighted, very full and on off. Rizwan looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Much better from Jacks.
On middle, blocked off the back foot.
Flatter and on off. Rizwan keeps it out.
SIX! Rizwan not letting Jacks settle at all. What a shot. This is full and outside off. Rizwan skips down, gives room and then smacks it over long off for a biggie.
FOUR! Saud Shakeel takes on Leach now! Tossed up, outside off, Saud Shakeel comes down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
On middle, nudged to square leg.
Tossed up on off. Blocked out.
Fuller and outside off. Saud Shakeel works it to covers for a single.
Flatter and outside off, punched to cover.
On off, kept out.
Full and on off, drilled to long off for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Rizwan chips it to mid on, uppish but safe.
On the pads, clipped to square leg.
Full and angling on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
FOUR! A bit of error from Root as he serves it down the leg side. Rizwan doesn't think twice as he sweeps this behind square leg for a boundary.
On off, defended out.
Shorter and moving in on middle. Saud Shakeel looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but height was an issue.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
Touch short, outside off. Saud Shakeel punches it through covers for a brace.
Full and on middle, kept out.
FOUR! Fifty for Shakeel! A wonderful knock under pressure! Tossed up on midldle. Saud Shakeel comes down and lofts it to long on for a boundary.
Full and on off. Saud Shakeel dead bats it.
Full and on middle, played back to Root.
On off, kept out.
Rizwan tries to sweep but this is very full, he misses his shot this time.
This time Rizwan sweeps it well behind square leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off. This is punched to cover.
Again punched to covers for a dot.
An arm ball on off. Rizwan stays back and defends it out.
Quicker and on middle. Rizwan defends on the back foot.
Tossed up, outside odd, this is the odd one which comes in. Rizwan inside edges his defense on the deck.
Outside off, kept out.
Flatter and outside off, Rizwan punches it to cover.
A maiden! Full and outside off. Defended out.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up, outside off. Saud Shakeel sweeps it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Outside off, turning away. Shakeel shoulders arms.
On off, blocked out.
Flatter and outside off, worked through point for one.
Angles a full ball on off. Shakeel rocks back and defends it out.
Floated outside off. Shakeel comes forward to push but gets an outside edge to third man for one.
On the pads, worked on the leg side for one.
Very full and on off. Rizwan leans and dead bats it.
Tossed up on off. Rizwan with a solid block again.
Around off, knocked to long off for a single.
On the pads, clipped to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up on off, defended to cover.
Touch short and on middle. Kept out.
Tossed up on middle, Shakeel flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.
This is full and on middle. Rizwan reaches for it and eases it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on leg. Rizwan sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Flatter and on off. Saud strokes it to cover.
This is outside off. Saud makes a big stride forward to leave it alone.
This is full and outside off. Rizwan leans and blocks it out.
James Anderson goes full again as he looks for some reverse-swing. This is outside off, blocked out.
On middle, blocked out.
Full and on off. Rizwan defends it again.
Ollie Pope comes close to the stumps. This is on middle, it is pushed to mid-wicket.
Short of a length and outside off. Rizwan splices as he looks to defend to point. The ball rolls uppishly but safe.
Flighted ball on off. Defended out.
Tossed up on off. Saud steps across and keeps it out.
Jacks slants it on the pads. Shakeel tickles it fine to fine leg for a couple of runs.
On middle, defended on the front foot.
FOUR! Jacks keeps on leaking runs. This is full and outside off. Saud sweeps it to deep square leg past the running fielder for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, blocked out.
On a length and on middle. Blocked out.
On a length and around off. Rizwan shows full face of the bat as he defense.
Full and on off, played back to the bowler.
Length and on middle, jags in. Rizwan helps it to deep square leg for a single.
This is full and angling on middle. Shakeel looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball balloons up and falls to the square leg region. No short  leg there.
Full and outside off, pushed to cover. Tight fielding from Stokes. Hard to find a gap there.
Floated full and on middle, pushed to the right of Leach.

JUST OVER! Tossed up on off, holds onto the surface. Rizwan goes inside-out over covers but toe ends his shot. Will Jacks from covers runs back but the ball just flies over him and falls on the deck. Two runs.
SIX! This is off the middle! Flighted on middle. Rizwan comes down the track and thumps it straight down for a biggie.
On off, blocked out.
Full and on off. Rizwan leans and blocks it.
FOUR! Runs flowing easily. Shorter and outside off. Rizwan punches off the back foot, past cover and it races into the fence. 12 off the over.
On a length and on middle. Shakeel keeps it out on the leg side.
This is full and outside off. Shakeel gets inside the line and blocks it out.
Saud comes down the track and defends this length ball back to Anderson.
On middle, kept out.
Angled on the pads, it is flicked to deep square leg for a single.
On a length and on middle. Rizwan blocks it out on the deck. That will be LUNCH on Day 5.
Some swing for Stokes! This starts outside off and comes back in late. Saud somehow manages to work it on the leg side.
Solid from Saud! Back of a length and on off, Shakeel lets the ball come to him and plays it right under his eyes.
This one does not bounce a lot! Length and outside off, Shakeel shoulders arms to this one. It just about gets to the keeper.
Attacks the off pole this time. Saud gets his bat down in time and blocks.
Good length again and on off, Saud plays it to mid off.
A maiden to begin with by Stokes! Length and on off, this is guided to point.
Just a wee bit of swing, some outswing, it starts on off and moves away. Rizwan plays it to covers.
Good length again and on off, Rizwan blocks it out.
Fractionally short and on off, Rizwan blocks.
On the fuller side, not a lot of movement, Rizwan plays it back to the bowler.
FOUR! First runs of this session. That is a wonderful stroke! Fuller and on off, Rizwan shows the full face of the bat, it is creamed down to the long off fence.
Uppish but safe! This is on middle, holds in the surface a touch. Rizwan plays a check-shot, it goes uppishly but lands well short of mid on.
Back of a length and on off, Saud blocks.
Good length and on off, defended.
Stokes goes really full, on middle, Saud gets his front leg out of the way and plays it to mid off. No ball signaled by the umpire as Stokes oversteps.
Just outside off, Saud covers his off pole and shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off and on a length. Left alone.
Two more! Length and around off, Saud looks to block, this goes more off the outer half through point for two.
A yorker to end then, on middle, Saud jams it out towards cover.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Anderson gets another one! This guy is an absolute legend, irrespective on the conditions, just manages to find the breakthroughs for his side. It is the big wicket of Mohammad Rizwan who just did not look like getting out. He falls four short of a half ton and England now back on top. This is on a length, it lands and moves away. Rizwan has a poke at it away from the body. He also plays it with an angled bat. It goes off the outside edge and it goes into the hands of the keeper. He maybe could have left that delivery but that is how Rizwan plays, he likes feeling bat on ball and that proves to be his downfall.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b James Anderson

Commentary: Good length and on off, Ali defends it back to the bowler.
Another length delivery on the off pole, Ali pushes it to covers.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Pushes at it with hard hands! Length and outside off, Ali ends up pushing at it with hard hands. It lands short of cover.
A dot to end! A successful over from Anderson. On middle, kept out.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Angled into the pads, Shakeel works it through square leg for one.
Length again, this is pushed to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and outside off, Saud Shakeel slams it through point. A welcome boundary for Pakistan and Shakeel who was bogged down a bit.
On the off pole, this is kept out.
Around off, Ali moves right across and keeps it out.
Nicely played! A short one, Ali gets right on top of the bounce and pulls it all along the ground through square leg for one.
On the stumps, blocked.
Around the off pole, this is blocked right under his eyes.
On the stumps, kept out.
On off, Ali gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Continues to bowl it on off, Ali plays it to cover.
On the stumps, Ali pushes it to covers.
A quick run! Fuller and on off, Ali pushes it towards mid off for a single.
Length and outside off, Saud strokes it on the up through covers for two.
Just outside off, Saud was in two minds, he first thought of playing at it but then leaves it alone.
Good length and on off, it is kept out.
This one tails back in from around off, Ali works it down to fine leg and takes one.
On off, Shakeel pushes it to covers.
On the fuller side, Saud takes a few steps down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, Saud lets the ball come to him and then guides it to point.
FOUR! Clipped away! That is a poor delivery! A full toss on the pads, Shakeel works it fine and this one races away to the fence.
On the off pole, kept out.
Angled into the off pole. Ali blocks it out.
Works it with the angle through square leg for two.
Back of a length and on off, defended.

FOUR! Between first slip and gully! Lucky boundary! Length and around off, this lands and moves away a touch. Ali has a poke at it, it goes off the outside edge between the two and down to the third man fence.
NO BALL! Stokes has overstepped once again! On off, this is guided to point.
That will be the end of the over! On off, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a lovely catch! Ollie Robinson comes on and strikes. Stokes can do no wrong with his bowling changes here and England now on top. They are just the one wicket away from entering the bowlers now. Saud Shakeel who looked solid out there falls. England are delighted. This is fuller and outside off, quite wide outside off. Shakeel could have left it but it is the length that makes him play the stroke. It is just behind a driving length. Shakeel stretches for it, it goes uppishly and to the right of a very short cover. Keaton Jennings, the sub, dives to his right and takes it brilliantly. England now 5 wickets away.
Howout: c sub Keaton Jennings b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Good length and on off, Salman blocks.
FOUR! Agha Salman is off the mark with a boundary! Length and outside off, Agha opens the face of the bat and guides it past gully and down to the third man fence.
Almost! Ollie Robinson goes for a yorker, he ends up bowling a full toss on the pads. Salman did lose his balance a bit but manages to flick it down to fine leg for one.
That is a sharp bumper, Ali does really well to move out of the way! No ball called though.
On the shorter side and on the body, Ali pulls it down to fine leg and takes one.
Length and around off, Ali defends.
Length again and on off, Ali defends it towards cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! Length and just outside off, Ali lets the ball come to him and then opens the face of the bat, he guides it past, no fielder in the deep and it results in a boundary.
Another one on a length and on off, Ali looks to defend, it goes off the outer half towards point for one.
Good movement! Length and around off, this lands and moves away. Agha Salman initially looks to defend but then bails out.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Three leaves in a row as this is also bowled outside off.
Angled into the pads, Ali works it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for two.
On middle, defended.

That is a beauty! He goes wide of the crease, angles it into the off pole and then gets it to leave the batter late. Agha Salman is all squared up as he tries to defend, he is beaten. The keeper too has to adjust as he was moving the wrong way, good take in the end.
Two more! On the pads, Agha Salman works it through square leg and takes two.
On off, kept out.

BEATEN! It is all because of the angle, Agha Salman is playing at those. From wide of the crease, Stokes angles it in, it is still a little too wide outside off and shapes away. Salman has a poke at it and is beaten.
Good length and on off, kept out.
This time he gets closer to the stumps and lands this on a length and around off, blocked out.
He really bent his back on that one! Bowls a head-height bumper. Ali moves out of the way.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length and on off, Ali blocks it out.
More runs! This is full and it comes back in. Ali gets his front leg out of the way and works it past mid-wicket for three.
Down the leg side, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, Ali pushes it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Ali drives but to covers.
Good length and on off, Ali plays it towards cover.
Angled into the pads, Ali works it through square leg for one.
Edged but a run! Fuller and on off, this moves away. Salman plays at it away from the body, it goes off the outside edge down to third man for one.
FOUR! Put away! It was a full toss but still needed to be put away! This is outside off, Ali caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Good length and on off, it is blocked.
Length and on off, blocked.
Ali takes a few steps down the track, this is bowled well wide outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Length and on off, Ali guides it to point.
Fuller and on off, Ali pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on off, Salman pushes it to mid off.
On the stumps, Salman keeps it out.
On the off pole. Salman gets right behind the line and defends it.
Angled into the pads, Salman works it to mid-wicket.
Around off, this is guided through point for one.

Three more taken! Ali moves right across and works this from just outside off through square leg. Three taken. Tht is porbably Stoke's last over in this spell. He has bowled 9 on the trot. Does he have the gas to bowl another one?
Good length and on off, Ali blocks.
This is well wide outside off, left alone.
On off, this is pushed towards cover and there is a loud shout of no.
Gets it to tail back in from just outside off. Defended.
Ali takes a few steps down the track again, this is bowled on the shorter side. Defended.
BEATEN! This one moves away, it lands on off. Ali is beaten as he tries to block.
Around off, this is guided down towards third man for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Another one outside off, not played at.
Around off, Ali guides it through point for one.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, it is kept out.
On the stumps, defended.
Length and around off, Salman pokes at it and is beaten.
FOUR! Put away! Fuller and on middle, this is timed down the ground and into the fence.
On off, kept out.
Outside off, Salman looks to guide it down to third man but is beaten.
On off, this is guided through point for one.
Around off, kept out.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
FOUR! Lovely placement! Length and around off, this is guided past point for a boundary.
On off, blocked.
On off, defended.
No ball! Another one! On off, this is defended.
Angled into the pads, this is clipped through square leg for one.
Another one on off, this is kept out well.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman strokes it to mid off.
On off, Salman blocks it out.
Fuller and on off, Salman strokes it through mid off for two.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Lovely stroke! Fuller and on middle, this is driven past mid on for a boundary.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Shot! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for a boundary.

NOT OUT! The dive helped Ali make it in! Fuller and on middle, this is stroked back towards the bowler who sticks his riight leg out. It hits his leg and then the stumps. An appeal and it is taken upstairs. Ali is in.

A LOUD APPEAL BUT TURNED DOWN! It has been reviewed. Seems like it is swinging a lot! NOT OUT! It is going down leg and the crowd erupts. This is full, Agha Salman takes a few steps down the track and tries to flick but misses. It hits the pad. A loud shout but turned down. England lose a review.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Salman works it through square leg for one.
On middle, defended.
On the pads, this is worked down to long on for one.
Floats it up on off, Ali defends it towards cover.
Another one on off, it is kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.

THE FINGER IS RAISED! Agha Salman has been given out LBW but he reviews. Is it too high or is it clipping the bails? Big moment in the game! NOT OUT! It is going over! England can't believe it! The crowd here is going bonkers! Agha Salman survives to fight yet another day. The last recognized pair continues to battle. This is tossed up on middle, Salman looks to sweep but misses to get hit on the body. An appeal and the finger is raised. Stokes really can't believe this is going over especially on this wicket which is slow and low.

DROPPED! A tough chance but England need to take those, they are behind in the game at the moment! Down the leg side, Azhar Ali looks to flick, it goes off the inside edge and to the left of Pope who dives, gets a hand to it but it does not stay in. A single in the end.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Down the leg side again, Salman looks to flick but misses.
Well bowled! A yorker on middle, this is jammed back to the bowler.
On off, defended.
A bumper to end the session. Salman ducks under it. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 5!
Very full and on middle. Ali comes down the track and pushes it to cover.
Flatter and on middle. Ali blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Ali prods and defends it.
Flatter and outside off. Ali punches it to cover.
Flights one outside off. Ali throws his bat as he looks to cut but misses.
Angles a full ball on middle. Ali eases it to cover. A maiden to start the proceedings.
Starts with a short ball on leg. Salman evades it well.
A bouncer, angling down. Salman thinks to play at it but leaves alone in the end.
On middle, this is tucked to square leg. Ali is long way down as he wants a quick single but is sent back. The fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end. Would have been saved.
This is outside off, left alone.
Short and on the hips, Salman nudges it to square leg.
This one lands outside off and swings in. Salman looks to push but gets an inside edge to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off. Ali defends as he comes down the track.
On off, kept out.
First run after Tea! Flatter and on off, Ali punches it to mid off for one.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on off. Salman prods and defends it out.
Flat and on off. Salman taps it to point.
On middle, Ali gets inside the line and pulls it behind square leg for one.

OUT! LBW! A huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. ENGLAND REVIEW IT. Desperate times for England. This is the stand they want to break. Pad first clearly. THREE REDS! Agha Salman is out. The 61-run stand is broken and England now are into the bowlers. A big moment in the game. This one is on a length and outside off, it lands and nips back in sharply. Salman stays back and tries to dab to third man with an angled bat but puts his front foot across. The ball pings the pad first. UltraEdge confirms it is pad first. Three reds are shown and England are absolute delight.
Howout: lbw b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: How has that missed the stumps? That was inches away from the off pole. WOW! A yorker, this one swings around off. Shah tries to drive but gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball just lands few inches away from the base of the off pole and goes to the keeper. UltraEdge later shows it did hit the stumps but the bails stayed intact.
Length and on middle, blocked out.
On a length and on middle. Shah defends it solidly.
All of a sudden the ball is swinging. This is outside off, easily left alone.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, punched to deep cover for a single.
Full and on off. Shah prods and defends it out.
Slants a full ball on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller ball on middle. Shah defends on the front foot.
This is full and on middle. Shah blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Straight to the leg slip fielder! Ollie Robinson is on fire, he has two in two overs and England can sense a win now. The last recognized batter, Azhar Ali is out of here and England are just the three wickets away. This is on the pads, Ali flicks but to the man at leg slip. Root takes an excellent low catch. Yet again the reverse swing doing the job, the ploy not to take the second new ball is working. This is going to be really tough for the bowling all-rounders now.
Howout: c Joe Root b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Excellent from Ollie again! A yorker, comes back in on middle, Zahid Mahmood jams it out well.
Bangs is short and on middle, ths is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, defended.
Bangs it short and on middle, this is blocked.
A yorker then outside off, Zahid jams it out to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
On the middle pole, defended.
Back of a length and on the stumps, kept out.
Shortish and on middle, Zahid defends.
On off, blocked.
Another over negotiated! On middle, this is played back to the bowler.
Yet another big booming inswinger, it comes back in from around off, Shah looks to defend, it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, ZM blocks it towards cover.
On off, defended.
Solid! Length and on middle, Zahid pushes it back to the bowler.
Well evaded! Shorter and around off, Zahid moves out of the way.
Outside off, this time it moves the other way. Zahid Mahmood has a poke at it and is beaten. An edge would not have mattered as Ollie Robinson has overstepped.
Solid from Zahid Mahmood! Length and on off, this is pushed to cover.
Good length and on off, defended.
On the stumps, blocked.
This lands and moves away from the off pole. Shah is beaten as he tries to defend.
On off, Shah gets right behind the line and keeps it out.

That just did not get up! A short one, Naseem was looking to move out of the way but the ball keeps coming in with the angle and does not bounce a lot. It hits him on the glove. Luckily for him, it does not lob up in the air.
BEATEN! An outswinger to end, Shah has a poke at it and is beaten.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
BEATEN! It goes past the outside edge for another time! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Zahid is beaten as he pushes at it.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one. A huge cheer from the crowd as the run is taken.
Beaten again! Another outswinger, this moves away after being angled into the off pole. Shah is beaten.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
This is full and outside off. Mahmood drops it to point.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Absolutely brilliant from Pope! James Anderson continues to serves it short, this is on leg. Mahmood tickles it, it goes more off the gloves and to the eft of the keeper. Ollie Pope puts in a full-length dive, stretches his left hand out and takes a stunner. He does well to keep hold onto it as he lands on the ground. Just superb. James Anderson gets his third wicket. England need two wickets now.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b James Anderson

Commentary: On a length and on middle. Rauf blocks it out.

OUT! LBW! An appeal for LBW and up goes the finger. Haris Rauf will take it upstairs. No bat there. Is it just sliding down though? Umpire's call it is. England won't mind it. They are nearing to the victory. James Anderson is showing his class all over again. What a champion of a bowler. He serves it on a length and tailing on leg. Rauf misses his flick. It looked like it will go down but the on-field decision is with England and it is enough for them to take the 9th wicket.
Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary: On a length and on middle, nips in. Ali blocks it out.
Short and on middle. Ali hops and blocks it out.
A length ball, outside off, Shah has a poke at it but misses.
This one swings away. Shah defends in the line and misses.
This one is angled across on a length. Shah is beaten as he looks to defend.
Outside off, Shah keeps it out.
Short in length and on middle, Shah gets an outside edge but he does well to play with soft hands.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length ball, outside off, it lands and swings in. Shah defends the wrong line and misses. That was close to the off pole.
Short and just sliding down. Ali fails to tickle it away.
James Anderson is bowling to the plan but Mohammad Ali is doing well to avoid the trap. Short and down leg. Ali lets it go.
Length ball on middle. Ali defends.
Full and on middle. Ali leans and blocks it.
A length ball, swinging on middle. Ali lunges forward to defend it out.
This one goes away, shorter and outside off. Ali defends inside the line again. He survives.

FOUR! IT GOES THROUGH! A BIG CHANCE! Short in length and outside off. Shah pokes, gets an outside edge. The ball flies in-between the keeper and first slip. Both Ollie Pope and Joe Root leave for each other and eventually, it goes through to the third man fence. Ben Stokes is not happy.
Outside off, kept out.
On a length and on middle. Shah tucks it to short leg.
On a length and outside off. Shah defends it to cover.
This is full and outside off, Shah pushes it to cover.
A bit squared up but Shah defends it out. On middle, it is kept out.
Short and this one stays low. Ali does well to dead bat it.
Length and on off. Ali blocks it out.
Short in length and on off. Ali hops and defends it out.
Full and swinging on off. Ali negotiates well as he defends it.
On a length and outside off. Ali looks to push but misses.
James Anderson goes for the yorker on middle. Ali jams it out well. Another over survived.
Samck on the glove! Shorter and on the body, Naseem looks to fend it but it hits the glove.
Was there something on it? NO! Shorter and around off, this one holds its line. Shah is beaten as he tries to defend.
This one does not carry! Frustrating for England! Length and on off, Naseem looks to defend but with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge but well short of second slip.
Length and on off, defended.
A short one now on middle, Shah spots it early and ducks under it.
Another over negotiated! On middle, this is defended.
On middle, defended. A round of applause from Naseem for Ali and says it is just coming on straight.
On the stumps again, this is kept out.
On the stumps, Ali defends it with his bat in front of his pad.
Floats it up on off, Ali manages to block it out.
Off the inside edge! Angled into middle, Ali comes forward and looks to block but this goes off the inner half towards the leg side.
On the stumps, it is kept out. Another over negotiated.
Angled into middle, Shah blocks it off. Stokes is running back to his mark.
On the shorter side, Shah guides it towards gully.
Another good length delivery, Shah guides it to point.
A waste of a delivery there! Down the leg side with the second new ball. Left alone.
Another harmless nut! Outside off, Shah covers his off pole and leaves it.
Solid! Back of a length and on off, Shah defends. A loud cheer from the crowd.
Solid again! The crowd getting right behind the two batters! Length and on off, Ali defends it out.
Another one on middle, Ali watches it closely and plays it right under his syes.
Well played again! On a length and around off, kept out.
That one does not bounce a lot! Short and on middle, Ali hops but ths comes at waist height. He manages to keep it out.
Really good carry on this one! Short and on middle, Ali though does well to duck under it.
Another one on the shorter side. Ali lets it go over him.
Tossed up on off, Shah plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter and outside off, Shah leaves it alone.

OUT! SHAH HAS BEEN GIVEN LBW! He reviews it! That looked very close. Will come down to the umpire's call we think so. NO BAT INVOLVED! IT IS THREE REDS! WOW! England have done it. The stubborn final wicket is scalped. This is full and on middle, an arm ball. Shah gets on the front foot as he looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and hits on the pads. An appeal for LBW and up goes the finger. Naseem Shah reviews but to no avail as three reds it shows. ENGLAND WIN BY 74 RUNS.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach
